title: sugar-free banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding and milk until thick; add vanilla.
Add about 1 cup of Cool Whip to mixture and mix well.
Add bananas, as many as you wish.
Pour into container.
Put remainder of Cool Whip on top.
Crumble graham crackers on top.

title: orange miniature muffins
directions: Mix sugar and orange juice.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add sour cream alternately with dry ingredients.
Fold in orange rind, raisins and nuts.
This is a stiff batter.
Use well-greased miniature muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
While still warm, dip them in the sugar-orange juice mixture.
Cool on a wire rack.
Makes 36 miniatures.

title: fruit cake
directions: Bake in 2 angel food pans, 1 1/4 hours in 300° oven.
I have mine at 250°.
Sometimes I divide the dough in 3 bread pans.
Put wax paper in pan first and dough next.

title: egg whip(eggedosis)
directions: Beat egg yolks at high speed; gradually add sugar and beat until thick.
Add beaten egg whites.
Should be very thick and creamy.
Add brandy or rum (this is optional).
Serve in cups and eat with a spoon.

title: buffalo style chicken wings
directions: *For hotter wings, use up to 3/4 cup, the amount used in Buffalo.

title: beer bread(raisin-cinnamon)
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Preheat the oven to moderate (350°).
Combine the self-rising flour, whole wheat flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves in a large bowl; stir together until well mixed.
Add the beer, the honey or the sugar and the raisins; mix until well blended.
Spread the batter in the prepared pan.
Bake in the preheated moderate oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until nicely browned and a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Turn out onto a wire rack to cool.

title: yellow onion soup
directions: Saute the onions in the butter for a moment.
Sprinkle them with the flour and as soon as they start to brown, stir in the stock.
Add salt and pepper to taste and cook for about 20 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. Shape into bite size balls and freeze on cookie sheet until firm. Store in plastic bag in freezer and bake as many as needed at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serve hot on toothpicks.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Set aside. In another bowl (large), cream together sugar, butter, Crisco and eggs (one at a time). Add vanilla. Mix flour mixture into cake; alternate with milk. Bake at 325° for 80 minutes. Ovens may vary.

title: moravian sugar cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cool to lukewarm and add next 4 ingredients.
Let rise in warm place about 1 hour.
Then add the rest of the ingredients (except last one).
Let rise 4 to 5 hours; put in greased pans, filling 1/2-inch thick.
Let rise again 1 hour until double in bulk.
Before baking, add topping to each cake. Dot with butter or margarine.
Push in small amounts with finger 1 inch apart over entire cake.
Sprinkle with brown sugar (1/2 cup per cake) and then sprinkle with mixture of granulated sugar and cinnamon sparingly.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 (8-inch) cakes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together the first 3 ingredients; add Rice Chex.
Stir until coated.
Put mixture in
a large paper grocery bag with 2 cups of powdered sugar; shape well until coated.

title: apple nut muffins
directions: Blend together eggs, sugar and oil.
Stir in flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Fold in thinly sliced and chopped apples.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased or lined muffin pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites, adding sugar slowly to form stiff peaks.
Mix crackers and pecans in the egg white mixture.
Pour into lightly buttered pie pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 300° oven.
Cool.
Top with 8 ounce Cool Whip.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake in 2 layers as directed on box.
Let cool.
Crumble 1st layer of cake in bowl.
Layer strawberries with juice, one layer of crushed pineapple with juice and 1/2 bowl Cool Whip. Sprinkle with pecans.
Sprinkle 3 ounces of thawed coconut. Crumble 2nd layer of cake; repeat layers as directed.
This should fill a punch bowl.

title: bunny's pumpkin soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Saute celery and onions in butter until transparent.
Add pumpkin, stock and spices.
Simmer over low heat 30 minutes to 1 hour, stirring often.
Just before serving, stir in cream and reheat.
Do not let boil.
Can add sour cream to each bowl.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Combine cake mix and Cool Whip to eggs in large bowl.
Mix well.
Add lemon extract and mix again.
Drop by teaspoon into dish of powdered sugar and coat well.
Place on greased cookie sheet 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake until light golden brown about 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: pretzel strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Watch closely.
Let cool.

title: elephant ears
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast onto warm water in a large bowl.
Add milk mixture and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough; knead until smooth.
Cover; let rise until double.
Divide dough into 6 to 8 balls.
Roll each out in the form of an elephant's ear.

title: hot crab meat appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for approximately 15 minutes, or until lightly browned on top, having put the almonds on top for the last couple of minutes.
Serve in a baking dish and use as a spread for crackers or for sliced raw cauliflower.

title: shrimp aspic mold
directions: Dissolve jello in very hot water, add all other ingredients, mixing well.
Allow to congeal overnight.

title: coffee bar
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cut apricots
in
small
pieces;
combine
with
water; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.	Meanwhile, mix flour, butter and
1/2 cup
sugar.
Press crumbly mixture into greased 11 x 7-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix 1 cup
sugar, cornstarch, and salt; stir into undrained apricots and
cook until
thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat;
stir in	remaining
ingredients,
reserving
a
little coconut.	Spread apricot
mixture
over baked crust; sprinkle top with remaining coconut.
Bake at 350°for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut into bars. Makes 27 to 30 bars.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 inch pan.
Measure the cereal into a large bowl.
Heat the marshmallows, the chocolate chips, corn syrup and butter in 3 quart saucepan over low heat stirring occasionally until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Mix in Golden Grahams.
Press mixture in pan using the back of spoon.
Let stand at least one hour or refrigerate for firmer bar.
Cut into 6 rows by 6 rows.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 36 bars.

title: quick beef casserole
directions: Place green beans in a 1-quart casserole, icy side up.
Cook, covered for 8 to 10 minutes.
Reserve.
Combine beef cubes and onion in a 2 to 3-quart casserole.
Cook, covered with waxed paper, for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Add tomato soup, 1/2 cup water, noodles, and green beans to beef cubes. Stir lightly and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, covered for 8 to 9 minutes.
Stir and let stand covered 3 to 4 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: nannie's beet pickles
directions: While working on the beets, mix all other ingredients together and let simmer.
Scrub beets well and boil until tender and skins start to peel.
Peel skins from beets and cut into chunks or slice.
Place beets into sterile jars and pour boiling syrup over them and seal.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Coat pasta with enough oil to prevent from sticking.
In blender, combine remaining ingredients.
Blend and pour over pasta.
Can also add green pepper, black olives and pimento. Refrigerate.
Keeps 4 weeks.

title: o henry bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil; remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Stir and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and butter or margarine.
Spread over bars and cut in cubes.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Mix in onion, parsley and seasonings.
Cut cucumber into 1/8-inch sections lengthwise and then into tiny cubes.
Stir into cream cheese mixture, mixing well.
Cucumbers will "weep" adding liquid.
Chill until serving time; overnight. Serve on cut-out shaped bread.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: *Melt margarine.
Use a small amount on the corn flakes.
Toss until moistened.

title: cheese cocoons
directions: Grate cheese coarsely.
Soften margarine.
Mix flour in it. Mix with hands.
(Can keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.)
Shape into circles and overlap one side over date (can put nut inside date).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter. Saute onion, celery and bell pepper until tender. Add red and black pepper to taste.
Add dash of Tabasco sauce. Add crawfish tails and juice.
After sauteing all of this until tender, stir in flour.
Continue cooking about 3 minutes.
Add water, bouillon cubes and parsley flakes to taste; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: ham loaf
directions: Cook at 325° for two hours or 1 hour if you make two loaves.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the pumpkin and the eggs together well and sift in the dry ingredients.
Fold together and put into a well-greased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour until a knife inserted into the center of the bread comes out clean in oven at temperature of 350°.

title: jessica's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove the stems from mushrooms. Mix crabmeat, melted butter and crumbled crackers in a bowl. Spoon into the mushroom tops. Place mushrooms on baking pan. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until tops have browned.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Put ingredients into bowl in the order given.
Do not beat until all items are added.
Beat well.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
This was Jim's mother's recipe and when we would go to Pennsylvania for a visit, this cake was always on the table ready to eat.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a large baking sheet.
Cream Snowdrift and sugars together in a mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.

title: garden tomato juice
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Press through sieve.
Add salt, sugar and paprika.
Chill thoroughly.

title: watergate salad
directions: Use pudding mix in dry form as it comes from the box.
Combine dry pudding, pineapple, whipped topping, marshmallows and nuts. Chill for several hours.

title: freezer corn
directions: Husk corn and cut off cob.
Bring all ingredients to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir once or twice.
Cool and freeze in pint or quart bags.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and Crisco until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Alternate flour and 7-Up; blend together with vanilla.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until cake springs back when touched with finger.
Use Bundt pan or loaf pan.

title: english toffee
directions: Chop almonds fine.
Melt butter in large, heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add water and syrup; continue cooking over low heat until candy reaches 290° on thermometer or until a few drops in cold water forms a brittle. Stir frequently.
While syrup cooks, melt chocolate in a double boiler.
Remove candy from heat; quickly stir in nuts.
Pour thin layer on cookie sheet.
When cool, spread top of brittle with thin coat of chocolate; sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
When set, do the other side.
Break into pieces when chocolate hardens.

title: grandi's italian lasagne
directions: Cook meat until brown; drain off fat. Add garlic, parsley, basil, salt, tomatoes and spaghetti sauce. Simmer 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally. Combine Ricotta and Parmesan cheeses; add eggs, salt and pepper.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.

title: shirley's beans
directions: Wash and soak beans.
Cook meat with onions and seasonings, then add
ketchup.
Mix
beans and meat mixture together and cook until beans are done.

title: traffic director's non-alcoholic drink
directions: Cooking Time: 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir together in casserole dish. Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: Mix dry
ingredients.
Pour
oil
and milk into a bowl. Add dry ingredients and stir into a ball. Make 1/2-inch balls. Bake on a
raised
pie
tin
in
a	12-inch
Dutch oven for 15 minutes at medium-high heat.

title: very berry salad
directions: Combine berries in a large bowl.
Carefully mix yogurt and almond extract with berries.
Garnish with mint leaves and chill until serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Empty 1 can beans into a well-greased baking dish.
Combine sugar and mustard.
Sprinkle half the mixture over beans.
Place 1/2 the bacon pieces over the sugar mixture.
Top with the remaining can of beans.
Sprinkle the remaining sugar-mustard, chopped bacon and catsup over the beans.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk in saucepan; stir over low heat until smooth.
Stir in chicken, chilies and seasonings; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Fill taco shells with meat mixture, lettuce and tomatoes.

title: watergate dessert
directions: Mix crushed Ritz crackers with 1 1/2 sticks melted butter and make a crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: easy pork chop bake
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on package and place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread 1 can of soup over the stuffing.
Top with 6 browned pork chops, seasoned with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Spread other can of soup over pork chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking 30 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine sugar and eggs; add flour and soda, then add vanilla. Last stir in fruit cocktail including the juices.
Beat well until all fruit begins to break up, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for around 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to boil and cook low.
Test in water until a soft ball forms.
Beat and cool until ready.

title: mom's special homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together lightly beaten eggs, sugar, vanilla and sweetened condensed milk.
Pour into canister, then add 1 gallon of milk to fill line on canister.
Stir until well mixed, then crank away or plug in for those lucky ones who have automatic ice cream makers!

title: cranberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Add beaten egg whites last. Bake in two 9-inch cake pans at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: beau's key lime pie
directions: Mix milk, juice and eggs.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Garnish with lime rind.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: incredible edibles
directions: Melt butter in microwave.
Add peanut butter, graham crackers and powdered sugar.
Press evenly into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Set aside.
Melt chocolate chips until smooth.
Spread evenly over mixture.
Let stand until chocolate hardens.
Cut into squares.

title: picadillo
directions: Heat oil in large pan.
Saut onion 3 minutes.
Add jalapeo and garlic; saut 1 minute.
Add meat; saut 3 minutes or until brown, stirring to crumble.
Stir in apple and next 7 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat; remove cinnamon sticks and stir in almonds.
Makes five 1-cup servings.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind vegetables. Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain off water.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add mustard mixed with flour.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add 1 quart dressing.
Bring to boil.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: chicken regal
directions: Lay chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: batter for deep frying
directions: Beat together the egg and milk, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Add enough paprika to make batter lite pink.
This batter can be used to fry onion rings, vegetables, fish, etc.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes drain; mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion, and cheese.	Pour over broccoli in 1-1/2 quart Casserole. Sprinkle Ritz over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes.

title: chow mein
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Brown pork well; add soy sauce, water, bouillon cubes, sugar, molasses and mushroom juice. Simmer 20 minutes or until pork is done.
Add celery, onion, bean sprouts, water chestnuts and bamboo shoots.
Cook until vegetables just tender.
Add mushrooms.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Serve over rice and noodles.
Garnish with slivered almonds.

title: hero burgers
directions: Combine hamburger, tomato soup, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Spread on 16 bun halves.
Place on cookie sheet; broil until done, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: alphabet salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain and set aside to cool.
Drain fruit, putting the juice in a saucepan.
Add the sugar and flour to the fruit juices.
Cook, stirring constantly, until this thickens.
Add the eggs and cook a little longer. Remove from stove and add the vanilla.
Mix this with the macaroni and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add fruit and Cool Whip.
Decorate the top with cherries.

title: blackberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and chill.
When Jell-O begins to set, fold in blackberries and pineapple.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
When firm, add topping.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Stew chicken; debone, if necessary.
Set aside.
Cook broccoli.
Place cooked broccoli in a large, buttered baking dish (or use vegetable cooking spray).
Cover broccoli with cooked chicken.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Cook until clear and thick, sugar, tapioca, water and vanilla. Blend together flour, brown sugar, oatmeal, butter or margarine, cinnamon and rhubarb.
Press half of crumb mixture firmly into a greased 9-inch square pan; distribute 4 cups of rhubarb evenly over that, then pour thickened syrup over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: buckwheat cakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add molasses and margarine to milk.
Combine ingredients and beat well.
Bake on a slightly margarinized hot griddle, turning only once.
Yields about 15 cakes.

title: melody dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a quart jar.
Makes 2 cups.
Once you make this dressing, you will use no other.
It's fantastic!

title: yogurt marinated chicken
directions: In bowl, mix together yogurt, garlic, salt, cardamon, chili powder, cinnamon and ginger.
Add chicken and marinate for 2 hours.
On broiler rack, arrange chicken in single layer, skin side down.
Place rack 6-inches from heat and broil, basting with marinade 20 minutes.
Turn chicken and broil, basting with marinade, 15 minutes longer or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli in greased casserole dish, 9 x 13-inches.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and soup.
Cube chicken and arrange on broccoli.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Melt margarine and toss with stuffing mix. Add to casserole and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine milk and lime juice in a bowl. Blend in beaten yolks and turn out into crust. Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Beat in sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spoon over pie shell, sealing edges.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: shortcake for peaches or strawberries
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Beat egg and pour into a 1/2 cup measure.
Add evaporated milk to top to make 1/2 cup. Stir into dry ingredients with fork.
Add a little more milk if needed.
(Batter should be quite stiff.) Grease small flat jellyroll pan.
Drop batter on in lumps.
Flour hands and press batter flat all over.
Bake at 375° for about 18 to 20 minutes. (Double for large jellyroll pan.)

title: pineapple torte
directions: Beat egg whites stiffly.
In separate bowl, beat margarine, egg yolks, powdered sugar and salt.
Fold into the egg whites. Put crushed cookies into buttered 2-quart Pyrex dish (reserve some for top).
Top with the egg yolk-egg white mixture.
Then pour the crushed pineapple on top, juice and all.
If too juicy, add a row of cookies on top.
Whip the Dream Whip according to package directions and spread on top.
Put the reserved crushed cookie crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients, except ground beef and ketchup.
Mix well.
Add ground beef and mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Mound loaf and place on foil or press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Drain; cover with 1/4 cup ketchup and let stand 5 minutes.

title: light and easy lemon broccoli chicken
directions: In skillet, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Combine soup and milk; stir in lemon juice and pepper.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender, stirring occasionally.

title: onion roasted spuds
directions: In a shallow baking pan, grease all potato chunks with olive oil.
Shake spuds and onion soup mix in a bag.
Arrange in pan. Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Stir once after 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare and bake Cookie Crust. Meanwhile, in a large bowl beat eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Immediately pour over hot crust; spread evenly.
Bake 25 minutes until firm around edges.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop mushroom stems and onion. Microwave until soft, about
4 minutes. Add cream cheese and breadcrumbs and also chopped bacon. Mix well. Put in refrigerator to cool for an hour.
Take spoonfuls, roll and stuff mushroom caps. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, until mushrooms are brown and toasted on top.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
Put potatoes in 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
For cheese sauce, mix together on low speed of mixer milk, flour, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add butter and Cheddar cheese.
Cook cheese sauce on High in microwave for 5 minutes.
Remove and mix with mixer.
Remove and mix again.
If not thick enough, return to microwave to cook longer.
When cheese sauce starts to thicken, pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: quick rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Drop into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake 15 minutes. Makes 12 rolls.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sherbet, together.
When ready to serve, mix in sherbet.

title: mother's double deckers
directions: Mix butter and sugar well.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat until light.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut half of dough with donut cutter, the other half with regular biscuit cutter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together butter, broken pretzels and sugar. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: bear bryant cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat firmly in bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish. (Mixture will be stiff.) Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over this. Then mix remaining ingredients and spread over top of chocolate chips and pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: heavenly hash(fruit salad)
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Set overnight in refrigerator.

title: aunt lucille's red hot jello salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in 1 cup hot water.
Add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water and applesauce.
Chill until almost set.
Stir in cream cheese and add nuts.

title: easy blender pancakes
directions: Put in blender in order listed.
Blend well.
Cook on hot griddle or skillet.
It will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and cut stems up finely.
Mix with bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic and onion salt to taste.

title: toffee candy
directions: Spray a jelly roll pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Place crackers close together on pan.
Boil and stir the butter and brown sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cover with chocolate chips and spread.
Let cool. Break in pieces.

title: weight watchers dessert
directions: Mix together and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: hot sausage-potato salad
directions: Combine undrained potatoes, summer sausage or salami and onion.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Stir in the Italian salad dressing and parsley flakes.
Serves 3.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Add oil, apples and nuts to beaten eggs.
Combine ingredients. Add to egg mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: nanny's corn pudding
directions: Add cheese, flour, sugar, salt and pepper to corn.
Beat eggs; add to corn mixture.
Heat milk and butter; pour into mixture. Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Grease sides only of 9-inch spring-form pan; set aside.
Mix crumbs with butter until blended.
Press firmly in bottom of pan. Chill.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese and 3/4 cup sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla until well blended. Stir in 1/2 cup sour cream and the chocolate chips until well blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 40 minutes or until 3-inch circle in center jiggles when pan moved gently.
(Cheesecake becomes firmer on cooling.)
Cool in pan on rack 20 minutes.
Increase oven to 475°.
Mix well remaining 1 cup sour cream, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and lemon juice. Spoon gently and evenly over top of cheesecake.
Return to oven; bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool completely on rack, then chill.
To serve, remove sides of pan; let stand 1 hour at room temperature. May be refrigerated up to 4 days.
Freeze for longer storage. Makes 10 servings.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
rice
and
drain.
Combine cream of mushroom soup and cheese in saucepan until melted.
Add broccoli.
In small skillet saute
onion
and
celery in butter.
Add to soup and cheese mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage and cheese set at room temperature, then mix with biscuit mix.
Roll into balls and bake on cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook celery in 1/2 cup water, just until tender.
Do not drain.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Place in 4-quart saucepan with 2 cups water.
Add cooked celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Mash slightly to eliminate definite cubes.
Add milk.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Heat in saucepan the pineapple and jello until thick.
Set aside and let cool.
In this order, mix Cool Whip, buttermilk and nuts to cooled jello mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: marble brownies
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter.
Beat together.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and set aside. Prepare cake like batter as directed on brownie mix package.
Pour 3/4 into 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over brownie layer.
Spoon remaining brownie batter in spots and swirl 2 mixtures together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk and stir in eggs.
Pour into melted hot shortening which has been heated in baking pan in the oven.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix soup and margarine until well blended.
Fold sour cream, green onions, Cheddar cheese and potatoes into soup mixture. Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over top. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop one rounded teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Serves 12.

title: old fashion vegetable relish
directions: Add pickling salt to onion, green and red pepper and tomatoes. Let stand overnight and then drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and place in jars and seal.
Cool pack and bring to boil and let cook 10 minutes in boiling water so jars will seal.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust. Put grated apples into crust. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over apples. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mom's sloppy joes
directions: Simmer all ingredients until meat is well cooked.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 6 x 3 x 2-inch baking pans.
Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and baking powder.
Add pumpkin, oil, eggs, nuts and raisins.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened and mixture is smooth.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 60 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pans and cool on wire racks.
Wrap in plastic wrap then aluminum foil and store overnight.

title: linda's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add to mixture.
Add vanilla. Divide dough into two parts.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: cheese squares
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan with butter.
Spread olives in pan; cover with cheese.
Add to beaten eggs, Worcestershire and Tabasco sauce.
Pour over cheese and olives.
Bake at 350° until firm, about 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: light and delicate dessert
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
When cool, spread with crushed pineapple.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup milk and salt. Beat until fluffy.
Add instant pudding; blend.
Add 2 cups milk; mix well.
Spread pudding mixture over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on last.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Use a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan with sides and lightly greased.
Lay out crescent rolls.
Bring up dough on sides of pan. Pat in place.
Layer in order:
meat, hash browns and cheese evenly over the crescent rolls.
Mix eggs, milk and spices and pour carefully over layers.
Let eggs settle.
Then bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Times will vary.
(Eggs need to be firm.)
Cool slightly and cut in squares.
Serve with fresh fruit salad.
Enjoy!

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix gelatine and water together.
Drain pineapple.
Add sugar to the pineapple syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Pour this into the gelatine.
Add crushed pineapple and cottage cheese.
Add the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: 6 layer dinner
directions: Layer each, seasoning each layer.
Pour tomatoes over top. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 3/4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: red cucumber pickles
directions: Peel and core cucumbers.
Cut into chunks or rings.
Cover with water to which pickling lime has been added.
Let set 24 hours.
Drain and rinse well.
Put in ice water to cover.
Let set 2 hours.

title: sparkling party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over ice in punch bowl.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Sift together the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir into first mixture.
Form into balls about the size of walnuts. Roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10
minutes.

title: baked italian zucchini
directions: Pour tomato sauce over first 6 ingredients.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover.
Add bread and grated cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: egg custards (2)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes, mix with flour, set aside for a few minutes.
Add onion, eggs and salt and pepper to taste and mix well.
Make into real thin pancakes.
Fry on hot skillet in heated oil.

title: turkey soup - parmentier
directions: Cook onion and potatoes in turkey broth about 20 minutes; add peas and carrots.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Add butter, liquids, herbs and salt and pepper to taste.
Add turkey and heat.
Serve with a sprinkling of paprika and parsley and the croutons.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bavarian chocolate mints
directions: Melt first three ingredients in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Beat on low for 1 minute. Then on high speed for 1 minute.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes. Beat every 5 minutes by hand.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: peasant salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss together the lettuce and the celery. Layer all remaining ingredients in the exact order listed.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 8 hours before serving.

title: apple stuffed pork chops
directions: Combine bread cubes, apple, cheese and raisins.
Sprinkle with salt and cinnamon.
Add orange juice and butter.
Stir until bread cubes are coated.

title: deep fried kudzu
directions: Use enough to cover leaf.
You may want to add spices to flour, also.

title: double cornbread(9 to 12 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Blend all ingredients except whole kernel corn, about 20 seconds.
Beat vigorously one minute.
Stir in whole kernel corn.
Pour into pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Beat softened butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat. Mix all dry ingredients (flour and seasonings).
Alternate adding dry ingredients and whiskey to the butter, sugar and egg mixture. Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add candies, dates and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for approximately 20 minutes.
Store in airtight container for moist cookies.
Add a piece of apple to container for even softer cookies.

title: rice pudding
directions: Separate eggs and add sugar, salt, milk, vanilla to egg yolks. Beat egg whites stiff, fold into yolk mixture. Add in cooked rice. Pour into 1 1/2 qt baking dish. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop and saute vegetables in olive oil.
Add raw hamburger, celery seed and remaining ingredients.
Stir and simmer until desired thickness.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Put crescent rolls flat in pan.
Spread out so they touch and form a crust.
Sprinkle on browned sausage.
Add thawed hash browns and pour mixed eggs over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° to 350° until crust is brown and egg is set.

title: cajun style sweet potatoes
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over high heat, bring potatoes and enough water to cover to boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, covered, ??? minutes until potatoes are just tender; drain.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese and milk until fluffy.
Add peanut butter and powdered sugar; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust or one of your choice.
Top with peanuts. Refrigerate.

title: 5 day sweet pickles
directions: 1st Day:
Put cucumbers (not more than 2-inches in diameter) in crock.
Mix 2 quarts of cold water and 1 cup pickling salt. Pour over cucumbers and cover.

title: salmonettes
directions: Mix salmon and egg in a bowl. Add Bisquick mix
and stir. Heat oil in skillet and drop salmon mixture by tablespoonfuls into skillet. Flatten each salmonette with spatula. Cook each side until brown, around 2 to 3 minutes per side.
Cook on stove top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in mixer until foamy.
Beat in sugar, zucchini, oil and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients except sesame seed. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Sprinkle top with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/4 hours (until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean).
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: grouper chowder
directions: Gently heat milk with cans of soup.
Add grouper bits and cook 10 minutes.
Add potato flakes and other ingredients.
Continue cooking gently another 8 minutes.
Chill.
At serving time, heat portions in individual bowls in the microwave oven.

title: barbecued pork tenderloin
directions: Mix marinade ingredients and marinate pork at least 1 hour. Line baking pan with aluminum foil.
Bake at 450° for about 25 minutes.

title: homemade brownies
directions: Melt shortening and cocoa together.
Blend sugar, egg and stir into melted chocolate mixture. Beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour batter into 9-inch square pan which has been coated with shortening.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: fudge pie
directions: Add eggs and sugar.
Beat well.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oreo mint dessert
directions: Crush one large package of Oreo (minus 1 cup) cookies and mix with melted margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften 1/2 gallon ice cream and pour over crust.
Refreeze.
Then pour a jar of Hershey's fudge over re-hardened ice cream.
Spread Cool Whip on top and refreeze, after sprinkling with reserved crushed Oreos.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil, then cover and cook for 3 minutes until forms a soft ball in water.
Add vanilla and cool for 15 minutes.
Beat until creamy.

title: slush
directions: Boil water and sugar and let cool!
Add all other ingredients, except 7-Up.
Mix and freeze in a plastic ice cream pail.
When frozen, ready to use.
Use 1 part slush to 1 part 7-Up in glass and stir!

title: easy creamy caramel pie
directions: Place the whole can of milk in sauce pan and put enough water in the pan to cover can completely.
Boil about 3 hours turning every 30 minutes with tongs.
Add hot water as need to keep the can of milk covered at all times.
After 3 hours, take can out and set aside for at least 4 hours.
Best to do this the day before you need it.
When cooled, open can and with spatula, spoon caramel filling out into crust.

Top with cool whip and chill over night. Can do two or three cans at once and mark cans when cooled and place in cabinet until the next time you want to make this pie. Just open can, spoon into crust top with cool whip and chill and you have a pie in 5 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: noodles riviera
directions: Fry meat and drain.
Add diced onion, pepper, spices and spaghetti sauce; set aside.
Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, Parmesan and parsley; set aside.
Cook and drain egg noodles.

title: honey poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix the 6 dry ingredients. Add vinegar and honey. Immediately beat with an electric mixer on low. Add oil slowly in small amounts. Continue mixing on medium, then increase to high speed as it thickens. Refrigerate. Holds well.

title: five bean baked beans
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Saute celery and onion in butter. Mix together the beans, celery, onion and sausage.
Heat the remaining ingredients in skillet used to cook sausage, celery and onion.
Add warm mixture to beans and sausage mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a covered container.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions in salted water until tender; drain.
Arrange stalks in greased 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken atop.
Combine mayonnaise, soup and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until heated.
Trim with pimento strips if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Pour into a square well buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle top with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: stovies
directions: Peel and slice vegetables.
Place baking grease in bottom of large iron skillet.
Layer in this order in frypan: potatoes, onions (sprinkle with salt, pepper and parsley).
Repeat.
After all layers go on, pour water over.
Cover skillet and cook on medium heat for about 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple cheeseball
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add 1 cup pecans and mix well. Refrigerate until firm, then shape into ball.
Roll in remaining pecans before serving.
Very good with Town House crackers.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: crab imperial
directions: Make a white sauce with the flour, butter and milk.
Add the seasonings and then the crab.
Place in a baking dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add the sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture and chill overnight or in the freezer for several hours.
Roll small portions out on lightly floured surface.
Use cutters to make cutouts of your choice.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Buttercream Frosting and decorate. Makes 6 dozen.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Beat in egg and molasses. Mix remaining dry ingredients together and add to form a stiff dough.
Roll into walnut size balls and roll balls in granulated sugar.
Place on cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
They will flatten out when baked.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: savory onion chuck roast
directions: Place roast in center of large piece of foil in roasting pan, pulling up sides of foil.
Brush A.1. sauce over meat.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and mushrooms.
Add liquid, then continue pulling foil over roast and fold over each other.
Bake at 350°.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Put chicken (preferably white meat) in bowl.
Add other ingredients, tossing lightly.
Chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hawaiian chicken or shrimp
directions: Mix together the chicken/shrimp, cashews, celery and green onions.
Then mix the soup, milk and noodles (save 3 tablespoons of the noodles to sprinkle on top).
Combine the two mixtures and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with the remaining noodles and the dash of paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter and cream cheese with confectioners sugar, then add Cool Whip and mix until blended.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Chill 5 to 6 hours.

title: sausage roll
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Roll dough to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thickness.
Mix sausage and cheese, place mixture into dough and fold all 4 sides around mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: kahlua
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 2 hours; cool to room temperature. Add 1 quart vodka.
Wait 30 days.
Serve with cream to make Sombreros.
Enjoy.
Also makes good Christmas gifts.

title: no-bake orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll mixture into balls, then roll in coconut.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and slice chicken.
Cook broccoli until tender; drain. Arrange broccoli in 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Place chicken on broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Boil sliced carrots (or use whole baby carrots) in salted water until tender.
Cool.
Place carrots, pepper and onion in bowl. Make marinade of remaining ingredients, whisking until blended. Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
Serve cold.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add the syrup and salt.
Beat well. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add pecans. Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pie pan. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1/4 cup sugar until thick and cream colored.
Gradually add milk, cream, vanilla, salt and 1/8 teaspoon of nutmeg.
Beat again until frothy.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In large kettle cover beans with water.
Boil.
Turn off stove; let sit 1 hour.
Drain water; add 1 quart water and chicken broth.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Add remaining vegetables and spices and cook 1/2 hour.
Add spaghetti 10 minutes before serving.
Add tomato juice, if needed, for moisture.

title: cream puffs
directions: Combine water, salt and butter in saucepan; bring to boiling point.
Add flour all at once and cook, stirring constantly until mixture leaves the sides of the pan clean.
Cool; add eggs, one at a time, beating each in thoroughly.
Drop by tablespoon a little distance apart on greased baking sheets; bake in hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat (350°) and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Puffs should bake until no beads of moisture can be seen on them.
Cool; cut top out.
Fill with whipped cream.
Replace top.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: tuscan soup
directions: In 4 qt. pot over medium heat, cook onion, carrot and potato in hot oil, until lightly brown, about 3 minutes.
Stir often. Add broth, water, marjoram, and pepper.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Stir in beans and macaroni.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes until macaroni is tender.
Stir frequently.
Stir in chopped escarole.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Melt together and put in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups crushed corn flakes, mixed with 1/2 cup butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Chop green stems of onions and meat together.
Add cream cheese and mix well.
Roll into cheese ball. Can be garnished with pecans.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Roll in rolls in wax paper.
Chill before slicing and baking. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes (ovens vary).

title: southwest spaghetti squash(makes 4 servings; carb count: 12 grams)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut squash in half lengthwise.

Remove and discard seeds. Place squash, cut side down, in greased baking pan. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until just tender. Using fork, remove spaghetti-like strands from hot squash and place strands in large bowl. (Use oven mitts to protect hands.) Add tomatoes with juice, beans, 1/2 cup cheese, cilantro, cumin, garlic salt and pepper; toss well.

title: spinach-pecan salad
directions: Whisk all ingredients together and chill.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt the chips and paraffin and mix together.
Drop onto wax paper and allow to harden.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Mix all spices and herbs together; set aside.
Wash and cut up the chicken as you choose and place in a large stew pan.
Pour in the beer, broth, hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Let sit for 30 minutes (the beer is a tenderizer and will cook out).
Pour the liquid out and heat up butter in a large frying pan (do not let butter burn).
When butter has melted, add the spice mixture.
When spices start to smell, place as many chicken pieces into the pan without overcrowding them.
You might have to make another mixture of spices.
Let the chicken cook until it is brown on the side. Turn over; cook the other side.
Repeat until all chicken is cooked.
Place the chicken on a cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until chicken is done.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt in bowl. Blend in milk and margarine.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: block party beans
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add onion, celery, soup, tomato paste and ketchup.
Simmer until tender.
Add to remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 25.

title: homestyle boursin(french-style seasoned cheese)
directions: Line 1 cup mold with foil.
Spoon mixture in, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Turn onto a small serving plate.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Prepare the broccoli as package directs, but cook only 4 minutes. Drain and put into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese over broccoli.
Pour the mushroom soup over top.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: chunky macadamia orange fudge
directions: In heavy gauge saucepan, combine sugar, butter and Carnation evaporated milk.
Bring to a full rolling boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add Nestle Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels; stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Add Kraft Marshmallow Creme, nuts and orange flavored liqueur; beat until well blended.
Pour into foil-lined 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: cranberry cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, orange peel, eggs and vanilla with mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Stir in 1/2 cup of the cranberries.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup of cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stewed tomatoes and okra
directions: Remove tips and stem ends from okra.
Cut okra into 1/4 inch slices; set aside.
Coat a medium saucepan with cooking spray. Place over medium heat until hot.
Add onions and bell pepper; cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add okra, tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat 15 minutes or until okra is tender, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
3 servings (serving size 1 cup).

title: sweet pickles made from kosher dills
directions: Rinse pickles and jar thoroughly.
Slice dills to your desire. Bring sugar, vinegar and cloves to a boil; simmer for 5 minutes. Pour over pickles.
(You may add 1 tablespoon Tabasco sauce if you desire.
Good without it.)

title: spicy crackers
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers.
Add crackers; stir to coat.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 300°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: In large iron skillet, cook bacon until done.
Remove from skillet.
In bowl, sprinkle sugar over tomatoes.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and flour over tomatoes, toss until tomatoes are coated with flour.
Place on medium heat, cook in bacon fat in skillet and cook until done.
Place on paper towel to absorb extra grease.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in shortening until soft.
Cook rice and defrost broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together in 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle onion rings on top.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Lightly grease pie pan, 10 x 1 1/2. Thaw and drain frozen broccoli or cook fresh broccoli in saltwater 5 minutes. Mix
broccoli, onion, pepper and cheese. Put in pan. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 1 minute with beater. Pour in pan and bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season chops to taste and fry until brown in small amount of fat.
Lay in casserole on cooked rice.
Mix soup with milk and pour over chops and rice.
Cover tightly and bake at 350` for 1 1/4 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Combine macaroni, cheese, mushrooms, mushroom soup, pimentos, mayonnaise, milk and onions.
Top with crushed crackers and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Makes a 2-quart casserole with 6 to 8 servings as a main dish, 8 to 10 servings as a side dish.

title: aunt bonnie's cheesecake
directions: Bake at 300°.
Reserve 1 cup cake mix.
Add remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil to prepare crust.
Press 3/4 the way up an 11 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, 3 eggs and the reserved cup of cake mix.
Mix 1 minute at medium speed.
On low, add milk and flavorings.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into crust. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool; add topping.
Keep in fridge.

title: puffy french toast(serves 2)
directions: Melt margarine in skillet on medium heat. With electric mixer, combine milk, egg, biscuit mix, sugar and cinnamon. Cut each slice of bread in half diagonally. Dip in batter, coating completely. Fry 4 pieces at a time until golden brown and puffy (about 3 minutes on each side). Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and cinnamon. Serve with warm syrup. (Blueberry syrup is delicious.)

title: irresistible low-fat brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
In 2-quart glass measure with handle, combine Eagle Brand low-fat, cocoa and chips.
Cook in microwave oven 2 minutes or until chips melt, stirring after each minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients; turn into prepared pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: german oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet melt 1 stick of butter, 1 1/2 cups oatmeal, 1 cup sugar; toast mixture, set aside.

title: oreo dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Crushed Oreo cookies and butter.
Put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring a large kettle of water to a rolling boil with a dash of salt.
Add peeled, sliced potatoes and carrots and boil for 20 minutes, until vegetables are fork tender.
Drain half water and add milk to replace that amount.

Add ham, chopped into bite-sized pieces, sliced onions, celery salt, coarsely ground pepper, 3 tablespoons butter and 2 cloves garlic (which have been finely chopped and gently sauteed in 1 tablespoon butter) to soup.
Heat until soup comes to a gently boil.
Serve immediately.

title: rice pudding #2
directions: Cover first three ingredients with 1/2-inch water.
Bring to boil.
Add milk.
Turn to medium.
When it boils, turn to low and simmer 30 minutes (covered).
Remove and let stand off burner for 20 minutes, covered.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove seeds from peppers and wash peppers.
Combine rice, salt, ground beef, pepper, egg, milk and onion in a large bowl. Stuff peppers lightly and place in a pan.
Add tomato soup and water.
Cover pan; cook and simmer for 15 to 18 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Place in baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch).
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: starter for sourdough bread
directions: Mix together well and let set out all day or night.
Put in refrigerator in container with loose cover.
In 3 to 5 days, remove from refrigerator and feed with 3 tablespoons instant potatoes, 1 cup warm water and 3/4 cup sugar.
Let set out all day.
Use 1 1/2 cups starter to make bread.
Put remaining starter back in refrigerator.
Feed every 3 to 5 days.
Share 1 1/2 cups starter with a friend when supply is enough.

title: instant spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all items and mix well.
Store in a jar.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
May need to add more cracker crumbs to mixture if too moist.
Form crab cakes, 2 tablespoons of mixture to a cake (approximately 1/2-inch thick by 3-inch diameter).
Coat crab cake with additional cracker crumbs.
Layer in waxed paper and freeze immediately.
Yield: approximately 20 to 30 cakes.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender or cuisinart.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together lightly.
Gently form into small balls, 1/2-inch. Brown in hot fat.
Add about 1/2 cup hot water; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve hot with slightly thickened pan gravy.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and flour or cornstarch; mix well. In small bowl, mix 1 cup milk with slightly beaten egg yolks.
Add this to the flour mixture, along with remaining cup of milk.
Cook until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, butter and coconut.
Pour into baked pastry shell and top with meringue.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add ingredients; stir together.
Place in large lasagna pan.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese generously on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until 160°.
Let stand 10 minutes. Serve.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Roll into small balls.
Dip in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, soda and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Be sure to mix well.
Keep covered in the refrigerator at least an hour or two before using.
Roll out and cut as desired.
Place on a greased pan.
Let rise for 2 hours. Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.

title: scallop casserole
directions: In hot oil in
skillet, lightly saute scallops, cooking about 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove
scallops and place in shallow 9 x 11-inch baking dish.

title: excellent tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together and put in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Top with Chinese noodles.
Bake 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: squash fritters
directions: Wash squash and onion and grate with foodgrater.
Put in colander and allow to drain for about 1 hour.

title: barbecue turkey
directions: Place turkey in crock-pot with favorite barbecue sauce.
Cook until done.

title: baked beans
directions: Add all ingredients.
Simmer in crock-pot for 4 to 5 hours. Or bake in oven at 300° for approximately 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, shortening, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and milk together.
Mix well.
Add oats and raisins.
Drop mixture from tablespoon on greased baking pans. Bake at 375° until browned.

title: pizza deluxe
directions: Heat oven to 400.
Bake crust 8 to 10 minutes, or until very light golden brown.
Spread sauce over partially baked crust. Arrange pepperoni, mushrooms and green pepper over sauce.
Combine Mozzarella and Provolone cheeses; sprinkle over pizza.
Bake at 400° for an additional 18 to 25 minutes, or until crust is deep golden brown.

title: diet cabbage casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown beef with chopped onion.
Drain off grease.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Shred cabbage.
Add to sauce and cook slowly until cabbage is tender.

title: soda cracker cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, nuts and crushed soda crackers. In a separate bowl, beat egg whites to peak stage.
Add cream of tartar. Beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in dry ingredients gently.
Pour in greased baking dish. Bake 25 minutes at 325°. Cool.
Refrigerate until cold.
Cover with large Cool Whip and crushed pineapple. Top with coconut.

title: toffee cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add beaten egg yolk, flour and vanilla.
Pat mixture into a 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle grated chocolate over top. Top with nuts.
Cut into squares.

title: tex-mex roast
directions: Cover with water.
Bake, covered, for 12 hours at 250°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and season to taste.
In a bowl mix other ingredients, except chips.
Mix meat with mixture, layer in pan. Meat mixture and chips.
End with chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: carbonera(italian spaghetti with white sauce)
directions: Melt butter.
Add oil, garlic powder, salt, pepper and parsley.
Mix all together.
Pour over hot, cooked spaghetti.
Add grated cheese and crumbled bacon.
Toss until mixed thoroughly. Serve with a large green salad.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Mix sugar and sour cream.
Put on medium heat and add butter. When it comes to a good boil for 5 minutes, take off heat and add vanilla.
Mix well.

title: "sweet mustard dip" (for veggies)
directions: Mix and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve with cut up broccoli and cauliflower.
Can double.

title: iams green beans
directions: Combine soups and milk in casserole dish.
Add green beans and mix well.
Top with Durkee onions.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Stir together pretzels, oleo and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken rotel
directions: *Cook as directed on package for 6 servings or as much as needed.

title: easy fudge cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.

Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Mix in chocolate. Sift flour, soda and salt. Add alternately with milk, beating after each addition until smooth. Mix in vanilla. Bake in 2 (9-inch) layer pans, lined on bottom with paper, at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Mix all ingredients, except taco sauce.
Stir well in large pan.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and cover with taco sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Don't let it get too brown.

title: pot roast
directions: Coat roast with flour.
Put in deep pan with 1 tablespoon oil. Brown on both sides (burn, the browned the better).
Cover roast with water, fill until about 2-inches from the top.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes gravy and vegetables in one pan.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Pour cake mix into large mixing bowl.
Add dry gelatin, blackberry juice, oil and eggs.
Beat well with mixer.
Pour batter into a Bundt or small tube pan and bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine melted cheese spread and milk.
Add potatoes, vegetables, ham and onion.
Add pepper to taste and mix well.
Spread mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover.
Bake 50 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover; sprinkle cheese and cracker crumbs over top.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts and cracker crumbs are golden.

title: grandma es' pink cookies
directions: Blend margarine, cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla until well mixed.
Add spices and flour and blend again.
Add food coloring to shade desired.
Spritz onto ungreased cookie sheet. Add 1/2 candied cherry to each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of a pan. Combine all other ingredients except for berries. Pour mixture on top of butter into pan. Spread berries on top of mixture in pan. Bake at 350° or 400° until browned.

title: chocolate striped cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan.
In bowl, mix chocolate wafer crumbs and margarine.
Firmly press onto bottom of spring-form pan for crust.
Bake crust 12 to 15 minutes. Remove crust from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let stand until chocolate chips soften, then spread over crust.
Refrigerate while preparing filling.

title: wellesley fudge frosting
directions: Combine chocolate and butter in small saucepan.
Melt over very low heat.
Pour into bowl and beat in milk and vanilla until blended.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until smooth and spreadable.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Beat together Cool Whip and milk.
Add cherry pie filling, pineapple and nuts.
Freeze and use when needed.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Cook jello, water and 2 puddings until well dissolved.
Let boil approximately 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Let cool, add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: chicken cheese fluff
directions: Put Cheez Whiz in saucepan with flour and egg yolks.
Mix. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add salt, pepper, onion, broccoli and chicken to melted cheese mixture.
Fold in egg whites.
Mix all together.
Pour in greased dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oven french fries
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Dry potatoes with paper towels.
Toss in a bowl with oil, salt and pepper.
Arrange in a single layer on a baking sheet (nonstick gives best results).
Bake 12 minutes. Turn potatoes and bake 12 to 15 minutes longer, until golden and crispy.

title: perfect white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water (110°).
Combine hot milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups flour; beat well.
Add yeast mixture; mix well.
Add enough remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and satiny (8 to 10 minutes).
Shape dough into a ball; place in a lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double (1 1/2 hours).
Punch down; let rise again until double (45 minutes).
Cut in 2 portions.
Shape each into a smooth ball. Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Shape in loaves.
Place in 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini-tomato casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
In 2-quart casserole, layer: half of vegetable mixture, cheese, other half of vegetable mixture and croutons. Pour over vegetable juices and sprinkle with more cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan 30 minutes on 350°.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cake mix, sour cream, oil, 1/4 cup sugar, water and eggs in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Lightly grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Spoon 2/3 of cake batter into pan. Combine pecans, cinnamon and brown sugar; sprinkle over batter. Add remaining batter and bake.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: fat free cake
directions: Using a serrated knife, carefully cut cake into 3 layers. Carefully brush crumbs from side of cake with fingers. On each layer, spread 1 serving container of pudding, being careful not to spread to edges as it will squish out when you add the layers. Pudding spreads better when cold.

title: spinach dip in sheepherders loaf
directions: Mix ingredients except bread. Cover & chill. Hollow out loaf, keep bite-size pieces of bread from hollowing. Fill loaf with dip. Can refrigerate up to 24 hours.

title: spicy stuffed peppers
directions: Mix the rice, onion, browned hamburger, cheese, salt and pepper to taste together.
Stuff into the green peppers.
Pour the picante sauce over and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until peppers are done.

title: my favorite chocolate icing
directions: Melt cocoa and add beaten egg, then other ingredients.
Spread on cake.

title: brownie fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs light and fluffy.
In another bowl, mix flour, sugar and salt; pour in eggs.
Melt butter and mix cocoa in; add to egg mixture and then add your vanilla and nuts.
Pour in mixture and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Shake fourths in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in a Bundt pan.
Melt additional ingredients and pour over fourths.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn out on plate.

title: layered cauliflower salad
directions: Wash cauliflower; cut into flowerets; tear lettuce into bite-size pieces, chop onions, cook and crumble bacon.
Layer lettuce, onion, cauliflower and bacon in a 3-quart bowl.
Combine Miracle Whip and sugar; mix well.
Spread evenly over top sealing to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with chopped lettuce and onion.
Cover salad tightly and refrigerate 24 hours.
Toss gently before serving.

title: ken's omelets
directions: *Or any type of meat you like.

title: tomato-basil vinaigrette
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or food processor; mix thoroughly.
Allow to stand at least 15 minutes for flavors to blend.
Serve at room temperature.
Other fresh herbs, such as parsley, thyme or rosemary can be substituted for basil.

title: spicy apple cinnamon bread
directions: Chop apples first.
Allow apples to drain thoroughly. Beat apples together with eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend well.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean. Yields 4 loaves.

title: mama's meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper, milk and 4 tablespoons catsup.
Mix well. Shape into meatballs. Combine other ingredients and mix well.
Spoon over meatballs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer each ingredient in the order given.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: swiss broccoli bake
directions: Make sauce of butter, flour and milk.
When thickened, add 1 cup of the grated Swiss.
In casserole dish layer broccoli, 1/2 of sauce, 1/2 of onion, 1/2 bacon and 1/4 cup cheese.
Repeat.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together the butter
and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla. Measure oatmeal, then take small amounts and blend in blender until powdery.
Add dry ingredients and oatmeal to creamed mixture.
Place golf ball size cookies on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: polly's oven chicken
directions: Sprinkle half of onion soup on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place chicken (skin removed) bone side down in dish. Sprinkle remaining soup mix over chicken.
Dot with margarine. Pour milk over mixture and sprinkle paprika on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 400°.
Serve with rice.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box, add
frozen coconut, mix on medium speed.
Bake in square pan.
While cake is still hot, punch holes with a fork and pour
the cream of coconut over cake. Refrigerate overnight.
Top with Cool Whip mixed with 1 cup of coconut.
Spread on cake.

title: sophie's patties
directions: Mix milk, sugar, butter and cocoa in saucepan; bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and let stop boiling.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Add oatmeal; beat well.
Drop spoonfuls on waxed paper to cool.

title: fruited raspberry sherbet
directions: In large bowl, soften the sherbet by pressing it against sides of the bowl with a wooden spoon.
Stir in thawed berries and syrup, pineapple, cherries, pecans and marshmallows; mix well. Finely chop the bananas.
Gently stir into the mixture.
Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Freeze until firm.

title: pumpkin patch pie
directions: Place sherbet in bowl and stir until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 of Cool Whip until well blended.
(May add few drops of red and yellow food coloring for more intense color.)
Spoon into crust. Sprinkle with chopped Oreo cookies, pressing firmly into sherbet. Cover with remaining Cool Whip.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Chop cheese, preferably in food processor.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: chewy bread
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, flour, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Do not flour or grease pan.
Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cool before cutting.

title: hot wings
directions: Remove flapper from wings and cut remaining piece into two pieces (throw away flapper).
Place pieces skin side down in baking pans (cookie sheets with enclosed sides).
Cover medium with lemon pepper and garlic powder.
Sprinkle Louisiana hot sauce over them.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove, cool and eat with zest!!!

title: creamy corn slaw
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and toss to blend.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or longer.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco. Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift cocoa, flour, salt and baking powder together 3 times.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: pickles
directions: Fill sterilized jars with any of the listed vegetables or a combination of any.
Add the salt, mustard seed and garlic.
If you like them hot, add 1 hot pepper to each quart.
Fill jars half full of vinegar.
Add water to cover vegetables.
Seal jars; shake to mix.
Store in cool place.
Will be ready in 2 weeks.

title: lazy pie
directions: Melt butter in deep glass baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl, except fruit; mix well.
Pour into center of melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit into center of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (about 1 hour).

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: In a bowl, mix Thank You pie filling and broken up cookies. Pour mixture into pie shell.
Put Cool Whip on top of pie mixture. Refrigerate pie until ready to serve.

title: chocolate peanut butter truffles
directions: Microwave chocolate on HIGH 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Add peanut butter; stir until well blended.
Cool to room temperature. Gently stir in whipped topping.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Scoop truffle mixture with melon baller or teaspoon and shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in your favorite coating like:
powdered sugar, unsweetened cocoa, chopped peanuts, sprinkles or coconut.

title: pecan kiplings
directions: Cream butter.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla, cold water and flour.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Roll in waxed paper.
Put in refrigerator and chill.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Do not shape.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
When slightly cool, drop in powdered sugar.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Spread croutons in a lightly greased 9 x 13 pan.
Set aside. Brown sausage; drain.
Sprinkle sausage over croutons.
Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients.
Mix well; pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator; let stand 30 minutes.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese and melt.
I use ham instead of sausage and add chopped broccoli.

title: shoepeg corn
directions: Combine Shoepeg corn with flour, whipping cream, salt and pepper.
Mix all together real good.
Put the butter on the top of it.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown on top.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in order given in quantities desired.
Chill.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: apple-sweet potato casserole
directions: Cover bottom of casserole dish with 1 can of apples.
Place sweet potato patties over the apples.
Cover patties with the other can of apples.
Pour 1/2 cup sugar over apples and patties; dot with margarine.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: elda's no-bake cookies
directions: Boil together 1 minute the sugar, butter, cocoa and milk. While hot, add the remaining ingredients.
Shape for cookies and roll, or press into a pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in dressing.
In a large dish, put a layer of boned and chopped chicken.
Add mushroom soup, diluted with broth.
Repeat with chicken, soup and broth.
Top with crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
tags: cream of chicken soup or chicken broth

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Combine vanilla wafer crumbs and butter, reserving 1/4 cup for garnish.
Pat mixture into a 9-inch buttered pie plate, pressing firmly against sides and bottom.
Chill.
Combine lemonade and water in a saucepan.
Heat at medium heat, but do not boil.
Add marshmallows and salt.
Heat, stirring, until marshmallows are melted.
Chill mixture until cool and syrupy.
Whip cream and fold into lemonade mixture.
Turn into crumb crust; garnish with crumbs. Freeze.
When solid, wrap in foil.

title: pumpkin cake 1
directions: Mix sugar with oil; add eggs.
Sift flour with salt, soda and cinnamon; add to sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin.
Mix well. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake for one hour at 350°. Cool.
Mix oleo, powdered sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Put icing on cake.
Put crushed pecans on top of cake.
This recipe will serve 10 people.

title: italian beef
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low for several hours until meat falls apart.

title: caribbean fish
directions: Use
slices of trout, red snapper, bass or any other fish you like. Cut about 3/4-inch thick.
Pat fish dry; sprinkle with salt and pepper and brown it in hot oil.
Remove fish from pan.
Saute onion, tomatoes, thyme and vinegar.
Add about 1/4 cup water.
Put back in sauce and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with rice or potatoes and fresh spinach.

title: gram's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla; add all other ingredients.
Bake in 375° oven.

title: angel strawberry dessert
directions: In a saucepan, combine gelatin and cold water; let stand 5 minutes

title: savory barbecue sauce
directions: Saute the onions in butter in a large saucepan until soft, but not brown.
Stir from time to time and saute over low to medium heat.
Add brown sugar, lemon juice, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and ginger to pan.
Stir until well blended.
Add lemon rind and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer over low to medium heat for about 15 minutes until sauce thickens.
Add thyme leaves and simmer for one minute.
Makes 2 cups.

title: individual pizzas
directions: Turn meat in skillet until it loses its pink color.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings of your choice.
Simmer sauce a few minutes and set aside.
Roll out individual biscuits to about 4 inch across on floured surface.
Place rolled out circles on greased cookie sheet.
Spread with meat mixture and sprinkle tops with any grated cheese you have handy.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake 10 minutes.
Should have 10 pizzas or as many as you have biscuits.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together, then add beaten eggs.
Mix in buttermilk and soda.
Sift in flour, baking powder and salt. Add vanilla and lemon extracts.
Add just enough flour to roll on floured board real soft.
The softer the dough, the softer the cookies.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll on pastry cloth and cut. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches into baking dish, juice also.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over peaches.
Melt two sticks of butter and pour over cake mix.
Bake until browned usually about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot punch
directions: Keep hot and serve.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 400°.
Thaw pie crust 10 minutes.
Prick bottom and sides with a fork.
Bake pie shell for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
