Cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned.
Drain excess fat.
Add taco seasoning to meat.
In small mixing bowl, combine beans and 1/3 cup taco sauce; mix well.
Layer 1/2 of refried bean mixture in bottom of pie crust.
Top with 1/2 of meat, 1 cup cheese and chips.
Repeat, excluding chips.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes; remove.
Top with lettuce, tomato and additional sauce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sesame cucumber salad
directions: Put cucumbers in a colander and set over a dish to drain. Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and toss. Let stand 30 minutes. Rinse and drain well. In another bowl, combine onions, garlic, soy sauce, vinegar, oil, sesame seeds and pepper. Add cucumbers and toss. Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. Serves 10.

title: caramel frosting
directions: In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Add brown sugar.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the milk. Continue cooking until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. If needed, add a few drops of milk for desired spreading consistency.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Spread crushed Oreo cookies on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (save 1/3 for top).
Mix together cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar; then fold in Cool Whip.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla in separate bowl; then mix in with other ingredients.
Pour over cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining cookie crumbs on top.
Chill and serve.

title: pineapple plus
directions: Mix pineapple, cheese, sugar and flour.
Crumble crackers on top.
Melt margarine and pour over all.
Cook at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mushroom rice bake
directions: Combine ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes on until fluid is absorbed.

title: pepper steak salad
directions: Cut beef into thin strips; they should measure about 3 cups. Cut tomatoes into wedges and green pepper into strips.
In mixing bowl, combine beef, tomatoes, green pepper, celery, onion and mushrooms.

title: sad cake
directions: Put in long pan and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian salad
directions: Cook shells according to directions. Drain. Chop onions, pepper, celery, olives, salami, pepperoni and cheese. Mix with shells.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn; add all other ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Will be good for several days.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Saute zucchini and onions in margarine.
Add seasonings.
Beat eggs, add cheese and then add to vegetable mixture.
Separate crescent rolls and press into ungreased pan.
Spread Dijon mustard on crust.
Top with vegetable mixture.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes (finished baking when knife inserted in middle comes out clean).
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix well together.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: caponata
directions: Saute eggplant, onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in oil in a large skillet.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, ripe olives, sugar and vinegar; cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in hot sauce, oregano and salt and pepper; chill 24 hours.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 4 1/2 cups.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add bananas and dry ingredients alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened; do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans; bake at 350° for 23 to 28 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely on wire rack.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, salt, corn syrup, vanilla and butter. Fold in cereal.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry ripple ring cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Combine all ingredients except gelatin and flour in a large mixer bowl; mix 2 minutes at medium speed. Reserve 1 cup batter; spread remainder evenly in a heavily greased and floured 12-cup fluted tube pan or a 10-inch tube pan.
Blend reserved batter, gelatin and flour; spoon in ring onto batter. Using a spoon, fold gelatin mixture gently into batter.
Go around pan twice; avoid scraping side of pan.

title: randy's cubed steak
directions: Brown cubed steak in frypan on both sides; put in a large pot. Add 3 cups of water, flour, onion, mushrooms and dried soup; stir.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.
Cover pot while simmering.
May have to add water as gravy thickens. Stir occasionally.

title: turkey wild rice soup
directions: Crumble ground turkey into 6-quart pot or Dutch oven; stir in onions and carrots.
Cook over medium-high heat for 3 to 5 minutes or until turkey is lightly browned.
Stir in chicken broth, rice, poultry seasoning, thyme and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 45 to 55 minutes or until rice is tender. Place flour in small bowl; gradually add milk, blending until smooth.
Stir flour mixture into soup.
Cook and stir over medium heat until soup bubbles and thickens slightly.
Stir in pimento.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° until brown for 35 minutes.

title: chinese cashew chicken
directions: Combine liquid from vegetables, water and cornstarch.
Add chicken and pour into skillet.
Cook 2 minutes on medium.
Add vegetables.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add cashews and soy sauce.
Serve over rice.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together well. Add coconut and juice.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Freezes well.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, starch and water.
Heat cooking oil. Fry catsup and vinegar mixture.
Boil until thick.
Serve with egg rolls.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together well.
This makes a lot and keeps good.
To use, put 1/3 cup into a mug and add hot water.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt in a bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal. Add egg and almond extract.
Mix well. Add chopped almonds.
Mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Take your thumb and press down on the center of the ball to flatten slightly.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour half cake mix into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
(Meanwhile, melt oleo and caramels.)
Pour oleo and caramels over baked cake along with chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour rest of cake mix over top. Finish baking cake.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar over top if desired.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veal loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients and mix until well blended, using a large spoon or your hands.
Press into a loaf pan.
Cover with foil and bake for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes more to brown the top.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour mix ingredients into prepared pan.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Then top with buttered corn flake crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes more, uncovered.

title: chewy noels
directions: In 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan, melt margarine.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; stir in brown sugar and nuts.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Carefully pour batter over butter in pan.
Do not stir. Bake in 350°
oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Place waxed paper under wire rack.
Invert pan immediately
onto rack; cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, peanut butter, powdered sugar and milk with electric mixer until creamy.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into graham cracker crust or baked pastry crust.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the apples.
Mixture will be thick!
Add the apples.
Bake at 325° approximately 40 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: jo's celery stuffing
directions: Saute onion, celery and seasonings in butter until translucent.
Add stock; fold in bread crumbs.
Season cavity with salt and pepper.
Stuff bird.

title: shortcut frozen salad
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions; blend in whipped topping, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Turn into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and freeze until firm.
Slice to serve.

title: strawberry-rhubarb crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine the rhubarb and strawberries in a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with white sugar.
Mix together the remaining ingredients in a medium sized bowl.
Distribute over the top of the fruit and pat firmly into place.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes, or until the top is crisp and lightly browned and the fruit is bubbling around the edges.
Serve hot, warm or at room temperature; plain or ala mode.

title: pinwheel sandwiches
directions: Roll out dough into 2 rectangles.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: creole okra
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in bacon drippings until tender. Add okra.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes. Add a small amount of water, if necessary.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no peek stew
directions: Bake at 300 degrees for 4 hours. Leave - Don't Peek!

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix together in the order given.
Bake in a floured pan slowly in a moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Combine the melted oleo, peanut butter and powdered sugar. Mix well. Add Rice Krispies and shape into balls the size of a walnut.
Set in refrigerator to get cold.

title: california garlic pasta
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
In a large skillet, saute garlic in olive oil until browned.
Add green onions and mushrooms.
Saute for 1 minute.
Add parsley and basil.
Toss cooked pasta into the mixture.
Add bread crumbs.
Top with parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain.
Cook beef; drain.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour to mix and beat well. Pour 7-Up slowly to mix, then add lemon flavor; beat well.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Dredge fruit in flour.
Add salt, coconut and nuts.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in 275 degree oven for 25-30 minutes.
Store cooled cookies in airtight container about 5 days before serving.
Yields:
4 dozen.

title: bonbons
directions: Combine all ingredients except for chocolate almond bark. Knead with hands.
Refrigerate until cold and forms balls.
Melt chocolate on low.
Use toothpicks to dip into chocolate.
Put on wax paper.

title: lemon frosted gelatin salad
directions: First Layer:
One head lettuce (broken up) in bowl.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine eggs, flour and sugar; beat well.
Add milk, corn and salt.
Melt butter and place in a 8 or 9-inch baking dish.
Add corn mixture and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except margarine and corn flakes. Place in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour margarine over the top.
Sprinkle corn flakes over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Stir flour, pudding mix and baking powder together.
Combine egg, milk and melted butter; add to dry ingredients.
Mix well. Spread into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: batter fried chicken breasts
directions: Beat eggs.
Add salt, pepper, water and 3 tablespoons flour. Mix well until smooth.
Melt butter with Crisco in frying pan. Coat chicken in 1/2 cup flour, then in egg batter.
Slowly fry in melted butter and Crisco until golden brown, usually about 1/2 hour.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Wonderful!

title: apricot bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks; mix in flour.
Cover bottom of 8 x 8-inch with 1/2 of mixture.
Spread on preserves and nuts. Top with other 1/2 of mixture.
Cook for about 40 minutes or until brown in 350° oven.
Cut into squares.

title: french pizza
directions: Dice olives,
green pepper and onion.
Add tomato sauce and paste.
Combine with CASHEW CHEESE.
Spread on whole wheat French rolls.
Broil until toasted.
Serves 15.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar. Add onion juice and mix thoroughly. Add oil slowly, beating constantly on slow speed until thick. Add poppy seed and refrigerate.

title: apple cinnamon jelly
directions: In a 6 to 8-quart saucepan, combine apple juice and pectin.
On high heat, bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Quickly add sugar.
Bring to full rolling boil and boil hard for one minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, sprinkle in cinnamon and stir.
Immediately fill hot half-pint jars.
Place hot lids on jars and close tightly.
(Can process in water canner or just turn upside down for a while to seal.)

title: pasta in creamy dill sauce
directions: Melt butter with garlic in pan.
Add cream, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Reduce heat; add fresh dill and diced tomatoes.
Remove from heat and gently pour over pasta.
Excellent over spinach fettucini or other flavored pastas.

title: pork adobo
directions: Put meat in skillet. Mix ingredients and pour over meat. Stir; cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender. Serve on rice.

title: chicken-and-vegetable platter
directions: Arrange frozen vegetables on a microwave-safe round 12-inch platter.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Vent and microwave at High 4 minutes.
Sprinkle lemon juice, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and 1/4 teaspoon basil over vegetables, stirring gently.
Push vegetables to center, leaving a 3-inch border.
Sprinkle chicken with remaining salt, pepper and basil; arrange chicken around vegetables with thickest portion to outside.
Sprinkle with green onions.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap; microwave at High 8 to 9 minutes, or until chicken is tender, giving platter a half turn after 4 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Drain liquid from platter.

title: rice pudding
directions: Pour rice slowly into rapidly boiling water in large pot.
Do not stir.
Cover tightly and cook exactly 7 minutes (water will be absorbed).
Add milk and butter.
Stir a little.
Bring to a boil. Cover and cook slowly over a low flame for approximately 1 hour. Meanwhile, beat eggs; add sugar, raisins and vanilla slowly until rice starts to thicken.
Serve warm or cold with cinnamon (optional).
Serves 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, 1/2 cup hot water, salt and yeast cake. (If you use dry yeast mix with 1/4 cup cold water and add the other 1/4 cup water later instead of 1/2 cup cold water.)
Beat egg and add 1/2 of the flour and cold water.
Beat thoroughly and add the rest of the flour.
Mix and put in a tight container overnight in the refrigerator.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch strips, then in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Melt real butter.
Dip each dough square in butter and lay in tube (angel food) pan.
Fit the pieces together.
Make two layers.
Let rise 2 hours before baking. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Combine salt, pepper, onion, mushrooms and tomato sauce. Pour over steak. Bake at 350° for 1-1/2 hours.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Squeeze water from spinach.
Melt butter.
Put spinach, onion, melted butter and sauteed mushrooms in casserole.
Top with white Cheddar cheese and bake.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles, but do not overcook.
Drain tuna and mix mushroom soup and tuna with noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: strawberry milkshake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend for about 30 seconds or until smooth and fluffy.

title: beef parmesan
directions: Pound meat thin.
Dip in egg, then in cheese-crumb mixture. Brown in oil, then place in shallow wide baking dish.

title: smothered round country steak
directions: Salt, pepper and coat steak in flour.
Brown quickly in hot deep fat, turning often to prevent scorching.
Place steak in large baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of flour on hot steak with 1/4 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Pour water over steak.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: easy nut bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Let sit for 20 minutes. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and continue cooling on rack.

title: old-fashioned cupcakes
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Cream together the fat, milk, egg and vanilla.
Mix with dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in muffin tins at 374° until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 6 cupcakes.

title: cranberry star mold
directions: In saucepan, combine gelatin and cranberry sauce.
Heat and stir until almost boiling and gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in undrained pineapple and ginger ale.
When fizzing has stopped, pour into 5 cup star-shaped mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold on serving plate.
Serves 8.

title: baby food bars
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Add cinnamon, flour, soda and salt. Mix well.
Add the baby food and mix well.

title: cabbage-carrot casserole
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots; cook until tender.
Drain and save 1/2 cup liquid for sauce.
Make sauce with remaining ingredients. Alternate with vegetables in casserole dish.
Top with blanched almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute chicken, onion, garlic, celery, green pepper and mushrooms until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add flour and mix well. Add salt and pepper, then slowly stir in chicken broth and tomatoes.
Simmer until thickened, about 3 minutes.
Pour over spaghetti.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of grated Cheddar cheese and bake in oven until cheese melts.

title: chitty chitty bang bang "fooj"
directions: Put all ingredients into a saucepan.
Melt slowly on low heat until mix thickens slightly and is smooth.
Increase heat; boil quickly to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; cool in pan of water.
Beat with wooden soon until thick and just until it loses its gloss.
Pour onto greased wax paper; spread out, mark in squares and leave to set.
Cool.

title: wesson butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Roll in balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press down with fork crosswise (like peanut butter cookies).
Sprinkle with colored sugars.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes at 350°.
They melt in your mouth!!

title: mint meltaways(candy)
directions: Melt butter; add water.
Drop flavoring into mixture plus coloring.
Pour over sugar.
Press in molds.
Let stand 24 hours in open air to set.

title: bacon horseradish dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and chill.

title: sunshine casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes.
Combine flour and 3 teaspoons tomato juice in a small bowl; add to vegetables.
After tomatoes simmer 5 minutes, brown hamburger and drain.
In casserole, layer vegetables, meat and cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Add broccoli and remaining ingredients, tossing well.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours. Serves 25.

title: steamed vegetables
directions: Cut
vegetables into small pieces.
Put 2 1/2 inches of water into vegetable steamer.
Put vegetables in colander over water. Bring
water
to
boil with lid on.
Turn off heat and let	sit 15	minutes
before
serving.
Season
with
butter, cheese, Mrs. Dash or wine vinegar.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add the eggs and mix good. Add the dry ingredients.
Add the sliced apples and sprinkle the lemon juice over the apples.
Add the cinnamon and the nutmeg. Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cocktail sausage
directions: Combine barbecue sauce, brown sugar and vinegar; let simmer for a few minutes.
Add sausage and let simmer until sausage is tender.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Cut together like pie crust.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: dill pickles
directions: Combine sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag; add to vinegar mixture.
Simmer 15 minutes. Liquid brine will make about 5 quarts.

title: tinsley's pound cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until light yellow (about 5 minutes).
Add flour slowly to egg yolks.
Slowly add sugar, then butter.
Beat egg whites, then fold into batter. Grease tube pan with butter, then shake about 2 tablespoons of flour around sides and bottom of pan. Preheat oven to 125°.
Bake at 150° until top of cake springs back. Then cook on 200° for 1 1/2 hours until done.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring water, sugar, cloves and cinnamon to a boil and let simmer.
As it simmers, add 2 tea bags.
Take out tea bags when it is as dark as you want.
Add fruit juices and let simmer.
Serve warm.
Smells and tastes wonderful!

title: barbecue pot roast
directions: Brown roast and place into Dutch oven.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add tomato sauce and rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Remove meat to platter; blend the flour and water and add to drippings, stirring until gravy is thick and smooth.
Serve with meat.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly.
Pat dry.
Prick with fork.
Wrap potatoes in foil.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Cut a lengthwise slice from top of each potato.
Discard skin from slice and place pulp in a bowl.
Gently scoop out each potato.
Add pulp to the bowl.
With electric mixer or potato masher, mash potato pulp.
Add sour cream, chives, garlic salt and pepper.
Beat until smooth.
Refill potato shells.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 2 to 3 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beignets(creole doughnuts)
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and shortening.
Add milk and let stand until warm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and add to milk mix.
Mix in egg.
Stir in 2 cups flour.
Beat well.
Add flour to make a soft dough.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick and cut in squares.
Deep fry at 360°.
Drain and glaze.

title: easy bologna cups
directions: Cook bologna in oil in skillet until slices form cups.
Fill each cup with beans.
Top with cheese cubes.
Drizzle with tomato sauce.
Cook, covered, until heated through.
Serves 8.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: With pastry blender or fork, cut Crisco into flour and salt. Add beaten egg with vinegar.
Slice through.
Then add 5 tablespoons cold water.
Slice through mixture.
Divide into 4 parts, roll out on floured waxed paper to fit pie tin with 1-inch hang over.
Turn under edge and flute.

title: mounds balls
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, vanilla and coconut.
Add milk and beat with mixer.
Roll into balls.

title: hot pepper butter
directions: Wash, seed and drain peppers.
Put through blender.
Mix all ingredients, but flour, together and cook 30 minutes.
Add water to flour to make a thin paste.
Add to other ingredients and cook 5 minutes longer.
Put in warm jars and seal at once.
Makes 11 to 12 pints (use a 2 or 3 gallon kettle to cook in).

title: crusty coconut pie
directions: Pour milk over coconut.
Set aside.
Cream the butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add milk and coconut mixture.
Put in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: barbecued baby beef ribs
directions: Wipe ribs with damp paper towels.
Place ribs in a single layer in a shallow roasting pan.
Roast ribs at 450° for 20 minutes, turning once.
Mix all above remaining ingredients together. Remove ribs from oven.
Brush ribs with sauce on both sides.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes longer, or until tender.
Baste with remaining sauce from time to time.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry honey butter
directions: In food processor, puree strawberries and force puree through a fine sieve into a saucepan.
Add honey and lemon juice and boil the mixture, stirring, for 3 minutes or until thickened.
Let the strawberry mixture cool to room temperature.
In a bowl, cream together the butter and strawberry mixture.
Let the butter stand, covered, in a cool place for 1 hour to allow the flavors to develop.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Sprinkle top of casserole with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Melt butter in a pan; squeeze in lemon.
Season chicken with your favorite seasoning and flour and saute.
Add oregano, basil and garlic powder; cook until done.
Cook fettucini noodles; follow directions on box.
Drain when done and add to chicken in pan.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: apple lasagna(makes 12 to 15 servings)
directions: Cook noodles, rinse and drain; set aside.
Combine Cheddar, Ricotta, egg, granulated sugar and almond extract in medium bowl; blend well.
Spread 1 can apple pie filling over bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer 4 noodles over filling, spread cheese mixture over noodles.
Top with remaining 4 noodles, then remaining can of pie filling.

title: shrimp mold
directions: *Can substitute 1/2 to 3/4 pound fresh shrimp.

title: "dog food"
directions: Brown meats and drain well.
Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
When melted, serve on rye or any other toast or crackers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, then pour over 3 large onions which have been sliced very thin and a 1/2 a peck of cucumbers, sliced thin.
Put in jars and process in water bath.
Makes 4 pints.

title: creamy dreamy chicken and spirals casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Lightly spray a 9X13 inch pan with cooking spray and set aside. Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add pasta and cook for 8 to 10 minutes, or until al dente; drain. Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat. Add flour a little at a time and stir until smooth. Gradually stir in milk. Bring to a low boil, and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in Cheddar cheese until melted. Stir in cream cheese until melted. Add wine, and season with mustard, nutmeg and salt. Pour cooked noodles in pan. Layer chicken pieces over noodles. Pour sauce over chicken. In a small bowl, mix cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese and butter, and sprinkle over sauce. Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes, or until edges of casserole are bubbling. Remove from oven, and stir to thoroughly coat pasta and chicken, and to keep top of casserole from hardening. Allow to cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients except the cup of chicken broth.
Pour in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Store overnight in the refrigerator.
Set out 1 hour or longer before baking.
Pour 1 cup chicken broth over the mixture and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: molasses popcorn balls
directions: Combine molasses, sugar, water, vinegar and salt in heavy saucepan.
Place over low heat, stirring until mixture begins to boil.
Cook without stirring until it forms a hard ball.
Remove from heat; add oleo, stirring only until mixed.
Pour over popcorn in a large bowl.
Butter hands and make into balls.
Makes 12 popcorn balls.

title: professorn's chokladkaka(the professor's chocolate cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 9-inch spring-form cake pan.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water (2 cups).
Add lemon juice and marshmallows.
Cool.
Add pineapple, pecans and cottage cheese. Put in refrigerator.
Chill until almost firm, then fold in Cool Whip and pour into a mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, then rinse in cold water.
Dice onions, peppers, cucumbers and tomatoes.
Add spaghetti.
Add Salad Supreme and salad dressing.
Can be kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: good stuff
directions: Tear cake into bite sizes, in a large bowl.
Mix the pudding following label directions.
Add all other ingredients and mix with cake bites.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: vegetable burritos
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Wrap tortillas in foil.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cut squash and zucchini in half, cut halves crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add squash, zucchini, carrot, pepper, cumin, basil, oregano and salt.
Cook, stirring 3 minutes, then add tomatoes. Cook 1 minute.
Add olives.
Assemble burritos, spread with 3 tablespoons beans.
Top with 1/2 cup vegetables and 1/4 cup cheese.
Roll.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serve with salsa, sour cream or avocados.

title: poor man's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, syrup and oleo, then add oatmeal and flavoring.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: clam chowder(approximately one gallon)
directions: Saute salt pork in large pot until rendered.
Add butter and heat over low heat until bubbly.
Add onions and cook 5 minutes. Add potatoes and cook 5 minutes, add water to cover.
Add flour, stirring an additional 3 minutes.
Add clam juice and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add chopped clams until well heated, then add cream.
Do not boil.
(You can use bacon instead of salt pork if desired.)

title: magic cookie bar or 7 layer bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan mix butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Layer chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour condensed milk over everything. Cook about 25 to 30 minutes or until coconut is brown.
Cut into bars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with stuffing in separate bowl.
Take half of mixture of stuffing. Cover bottom of pan.
Spread out all of the chicken on top of mixture of stuffing in pan.
Pour mixture of soups and broth over chicken, then spread rest of stuffing on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ground beef, milk, ketchup, bread crumbs and onions in large bowl.
Spread mixture evenly in pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Remove pie from oven and sprinkle cheese evenly on top.

title: wassail
directions: Combine sugar and 2 cups boiling water.
Boil for 5 minutes. Add all spices.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Beat egg and add sugar and flour and then add pineapple juice. Bring to boil and cook over low heat until it thickens.
Cool and add marshmallows, pecans and pineapple.
Chill and serve.

title: gourmet's chicken
directions: Remove bones from chicken; pound meat until flat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place cheese in center; fold chicken over cheese.
Fasten with toothpick.
Beat egg and water together.
Dip stuffed chicken in egg mixture, then dip in potato chips (cover well).
Place in a 375° oven; bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
(Cover for 30 minutes, then finish cooking, uncovered.)
Serve over noodles.
You will have 8 servings.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: Mix beaten egg with milk, Worcestershire, hot pepper sauce and 1 tablespoon flour.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix 2 cups flour with salt and pepper to taste in a separate bowl. Dip pickles in egg mixture, then into flour, then into egg and back into flour.
Fry in 350° oil until golden brown.

title: amish slaw
directions: Shred cabbage in large bowl.
Layer onion, then pepper. Sprinkle sugar on top of all and let set.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl until dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours until slightly thickened.

title: little pizza snacks
directions: Crumble Italian sausage in large skillet.
Add hot sausage, onion and pepper.
Cook until meat is done.
Drain well on paper towels.
Return meat mixture to skillet.
Add seasonings.
Heat on low heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Remove from heat.
Spread a scant tablespoon on each bread slice.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: easy coconut pie(this pie makes its own crust!)
directions: Mix sugar and oleo until smooth.
Add eggs, flour, milk and vanilla.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into two 9-inch greased pie pans. Bake at 325 for 30 minutes.

title: potluck spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving-size pieces; place with the meaty side up on racks in two greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Drain; remove racks and return ribs to pans.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over ribs.
Return to the oven, uncovered, for 35 minutes or until sauce coats ribs, basting occasionally.
Ribs can also be grilled over medium-hot coals for the last 35 minutes instead of baking.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: sue's western muffins
directions: Combine shortening with boiling water and cool.
Mix with remaining ingredients until blended.
Spoon into greased or paper lined muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes (a little longer if direct from refrigerator).
Keeps in refrigerator for 6 to 7 weeks.
Makes 6 or 7 dozen.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water about 30 minutes, or until tender.
Chill.
Peel and grate potatoes.
Combine cheese, milk and butter in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until melted. Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper. Fold cheese mixture into potatoes.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pan.
Heat over medium heat, stirring until dough forms a ball, 3 or 5 minutes.
Let dough cool a minute or two and knead until smooth.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix all filling ingredients; divide and spread evenly over the tortillas.
Roll up.
Cover with plastic wrap, twisting ends. Refrigerate several hours.
Unwrap.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices (electric knife works best).
Discard ends.
Serve with picante sauce or salsa.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan, using half of pastry.
Roll out remaining pastry to top crust.
Set oven at 400°.
Mix fructose, flour and spices.
Spread a little mixture over bottom of pies.
Peel and core apples into thin slices.
Sprinkle with remaining mixture. Put butter in small bits around pies, then put pastry for topping. Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: dill pea salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, salt, dill weed, sour cream and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Add celery, onions and peas.
Stir to coat.
Chill about 2 hours.
Serve on lettuce bed.

title: dumplings made with raw and boiled potatoes mixed
directions: Note:
If you want, you can press in each ball some croutons or a pitted prune.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar in bowl.
Mix in margarine to make crumb mixture.
Set aside 3/4 cup for topping.
Press remaining in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, pumpkin, eggs, cinnamon and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over baked crust.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: texas delight *
directions: Mix softened margarine, flour and nuts.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Chill.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine all ingredients, except the bread crumbs, and put into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with the bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes until golden brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy rotini delight
directions: Cook rotini pasta as directed and keep warm after draining water.
Combine beef, onion and green pepper and cook over medium heat.
Drain any fat drippings.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, mushrooms and all seasonings.
Simmer low for 30 minutes.
Fold in the cooked rotini and mix together.
In a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, layer the rotini mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 35 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
This is an easy dish to prepare ahead.

title: peach sherbet
directions: Freeze like ice cream.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Cook the lasagne noodles.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain. Add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for a few minutes.
In separate bowl mix cottage cheese, eggs and Mozzarella cheese.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the sauce, noodles, cheese, noodles, sauce and cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: carrots and apples(method:  one pot)
directions: Partially cook carrots (2 to 3 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients; mix.
Cook until heated through.

title: wheat chex bread
directions: Mix Wheat Chex, salt, sugar and shortening.
Heat milk in 1/4 cup water.
Bring to boiling.
Pour over mixture.
Stir and let cool until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in remaining 1/4 cup water (lukewarm).
Stir into cooled mixture.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Mix after each cup.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Set in warm place to rise until double in size.
Punch down and rise again.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump crushed pineapple in the pan. Dump cherry pie filling on top of the pineapple.
Dump cake mix on top of the cherry pie filling and cut margarine into pieces and place on top of dry cake mix.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: smoked cabbage
directions: 1. Cut the base off the cabbage and set to the side to be used later for a cap. 2. Dig a hole into the cabbage through the base but not all the way through.
Set aside "insides" for later use. 3. Brown the pork sausage with the onion and all the in gedients. Spoon the sausage into the cabbage shell.
Replace cabbage cap. 4. Wrap in aluminum foil and place on grill (medium heat) for appx 1 hour.
Any left over sausage can be mixed with the cabbage cut out of the center and wrapped in aluminum foil also.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Peel large cucumbers and slice thinly.
Roll in flour (cornmeal may be added).
Place in single layer in skillet of hot grease.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook on medium-high until brown on both sides.

title: nacho potato soup
directions: In a large sauce pan, combine the contents of the potato package, corn, tomatoes and water.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and cover.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add in the milk and cheese, stir until cheese is melted.
Garnish with parsley.

title: trout almandine
directions: Dip trout in buttermilk.
Dredge in flour, salt and pepper. Cook fish in butter until golden brown and place on a platter.
Add last 3 ingredients to skillet and heat thoroughly.
Pour over fish.

title: wild rice and shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions using 1/2 cup less water. Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheery cherry vanilla fudge
directions: In 2-quart glass measuring cup, combine first 5 ingredients. Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir well until sugar dissolves. Microwave on High 6 minutes (236°).
Let stand 15 minutes; do not stir.

title: creamed eggs on toast
directions: Hard-cook eggs.
Peel and slice.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook over low heat to make a white cream sauce. Carefully stir in eggs in sauce and serve over toast.

title: gourmet cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins and shred coarsely.
In saucepan over low heat, combine cheese and butter.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat and add sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Fold sauce into potatoes.
Pour into greased casserole.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: holiday strata(yields 8 to 12)
directions: Will also need a 9 x 13-inch greased Pyrex pan.

title: aunt emma's happy hermits
directions: May use chopped dates in place of chocolate chips.

title: bready bears
directions: Lightly grease two cookie sheets.
Cut each loaf of bread in half.
Divide each of the halves into thirds.
Use the first third of dough to form one bear's body, the second third to form one bear's paws and feet and the final third to form the head and muzzle.
Pinch dough together.
Let bear rise for 30 minutes.
Mix egg white and water.
Brush bears with this mixture.
Use raisins to make eyes, nose and belly button.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 4 bears.

title: remoulade sauce
directions: In a bowl, stir together the yolks, the mustard, the anchovy paste, the Worcestershire sauce, the Tabasco, the mayonnaise, the celery, the parsley, the bell pepper, the garlic and the celery seed until the mixture is combined well; add the egg whites and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve the sauce with boiled shrimp. Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: butterscotch krispies bars
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows together in a large pan.
Add butterscotch chips.
Do not boil.
Stir until melted.
Add Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Mix well.
Press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into bars when cooled.

title: june's vegetable casserole
directions: Into large casserole or baking dish, place in layers in the following order:

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place the thin sliced potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Mix together the flour with the 1 cup of cold milk, mixing well.
Add to the flour/milk mixture the salt, pepper and butter.
Pour the liquid over on top of the potatoes and spread grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: croutons
directions: Cut bread into small cubes and place in large bowl.
Mix next 7 ingredients and pour over bread cubes and toss.
Lay flat on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until crunchy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Cut up, then add sour cream, soup, cheese, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle layer of crumbs in casserole dish. Spoon in broccoli mixture and cover with rest of crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: grandma turner's chocolate pie
directions: Cook first 6 items in double boiler until mixture starts to get thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until set.
Add meringue.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet until meat is browned. Drain off fat. Add seasonings and the tomato soup. Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add cheese and cook slowly, stirring until cheese melts. Stir in rice. Cool.

title: summer picnic potato salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, prepared mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper together.
When potatoes are cooled, add vegetables, eggs and dressing.
Mix thoroughly and refrigerate for at least two hours before serving.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: turnip salad
directions: Add salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar to taste.

title: macaroni 'n cheese beef bake
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse.
Brown ground beef, onions and green peppers in skillet.
Stir in flour and add tomatoes.
Cook until mixture thickens, then stir in cheese, seasoning and macaroni.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Put in greased casserole and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly. Freezes well.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and oleo in microwave for 2 minutes. Pour over cereal.
Stir.

title: fettucine with shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Slice zucchini about 1/8-inch thick. Cook pasta according to directions and drain, reserving 1/4 cup of cooking liquid.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: pam taylor's mexican bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Add enough water or tomato juice to cover and simmer for 1 hour.
It will be thick. This recipe is versatile.
If you don't like one thing, then substitute it with a can of another thing.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Wash mushrooms, drain, dry and slice in half. Cut celery into 1/8 inch cuts and onions into 1/4 inch squares, put in serving bowl. Add bell pepper, garnish with julienne cut tomato in 1/2 inch strips. Pour dressing over top, marinate 30 minutes before serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: stuffed peppers(microwave)
directions: Crumble ground beef in medium glass bowl.
Stir in onion. Heat 4 minutes on High, until beef is brown, stirring once, then drain.
Stir in 1/2 can of tomato sauce, water, cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat, covered, for 3 minutes on High.
Stir in rice.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Blend in vanilla and prunes.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: quick bake beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix catsup, mustard, sugar and onion. Mix in beans.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place bacon over top of casserole.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter, syrup and milk in large saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour in buttered pan.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift, measure and sift flour again.
Add soda, salt and sugar; sift again.
Add caraway seed.
Melt butter.
Add beaten eggs and enough sour milk to obtain 1 1/4 cups liquid.
Quickly combine wet and dry ingredients.
Put on floured board.
Knead with tips of fingers lightly for 1 minute.
Put in greased heavy iron or other heavy baking dish.
Set in preheated 375° oven.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot with plenty of butter.

title: pineapple chicken stir-fry
directions: Preheat oil.
Cook on high.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix cornstarch, salt, water and soy sauce.
Dredge chicken; set aside.
Saute onion 2 minutes in 1 tablespoon oil. Remove from pan.
Saute celery and pepper in 1 tablespoon of oil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add water chestnuts for 30 seconds.
Remove from pan.
Stir-fry chicken in 2 tablespoons oil until brown. Return vegetables to pan.
Add pineapple; stir to mix.
Add juice and simmer until heated.
Serve with rice.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice as directed and barely overlap on a pizza pan.
Bake as directed and let cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Drain whole kernel corn.
Mix corns, add flour to both.
Melt margarine in milk.
Add sugar and milk mixture to corn.
Add well beaten eggs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Add crushed pineapple (drained).
Cut bread in small cubes; mix in well.
Pour in buttered casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter with vinegar over heat.
Add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
(Double for 2.)

title: caramel corn
directions: Spread the popcorn out on cookie sheets or cake pans.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Mix in Karo syrup and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and stir constantly for 2 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Mix in vanilla and baking soda.
Stir well.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix well.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for 35 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, cream, sugar, cinnamon and vanilla.
Set aside. Peel top off of bread.
Place on bottom of dish.
Cut bread into cubes.
Toast in oven about five minutes.
Place bread on top of crust.
Sprinkle raisins and apples.
Continue to layer until finished.
Pour mixture on top and bake until golden brown.

title: grammies
directions: Line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Break crackers apart. Place crackers on foil, sides touching.
Melt butter; add sugar and bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Add almonds.
Remove from heat at once.
Drizzle the mixture over crackers.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Let cool before removing from the pan.

title: isabell's potato salad
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into large cubes.
Cook in boiling salted water.
Drain when done.
Cut boiled eggs into small pieces.
Dice onion.
Mix all ingredients and add salt and pepper to taste.
If mixture is dry, add Miracle Whip as needed.

title: persimmon pudding(favorite recipes of jefferson's country)
directions: Select good wild ripe persimmons (best after a heavy frost) and mash through a sieve.
Measure pulp.
Add milk, sugar, salt, butter and crumbs.
Then add flour which has been sifted with baking powder.
Bake in greased individual molds 30 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serve with lemon sauce or whipped cream.

title: kris' enchiladas
directions: Fry hamburger according to directions on taco seasoning packet.
Roll hamburger mixture into the tortilla shells.
Put in shallow baking pan.
When all shells are full, pour over enchilada sauce.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 10 muffin tins with paper liners. In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients but baking mix, stirring with a fork until just blended.
Stir in baking mix until just combined.
Don't overmix.
Spoon batter into prepared tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Freeze cherries overnight on a flat surface.
Mix together other ingredients.
Wrap and seal frozen cherries in a small piece of the mixture.
Roll into a ball.
Place in refrigerator for at least 20 minutes.

title: johnny bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: chip beef dip
directions: Cream cheese and milk; add dried beef, peppers, garlic salt, pepper and sour cream.
Mix well.
Brown nuts in margarine and pour over dip in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased and floured tube
pan.
Bake at 325° about 55 minutes.
Cool until pan is warm to the touch.

title: pear honey
directions: Cook ground pears until tender.
Add other ingredients and cook.
Mix well, pour into hot jars and seal.

title: chocolate oatmeal drops or cookies
directions: Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Take off heat and put in 1 tablespoon vanilla and 3 tablespoons peanut butter.
Stir until smooth, then add 3 cups oatmeal.
Drop on wax paper and let stand until hard.

title: india chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken lightly with paprika and brown in a pressure cooker in the oil.
Combine all other ingredients and place alternate layers of chicken and combined ingredients in the pressure cooker, starting with chicken and finishing with rice.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain fruit and save pineapple juice.
Add until the mixture suits you.

title: ham chowder
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper. Simmer until vegetables are done.
Melt butter in a large pan. Add flour.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese. Pour into vegetables.
Add ham.
Heat thoroughly.
Add hot sauce, if desired.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil a whole chicken and season with salt and pepper.
When chicken is done, cool and take meat off the bones.
Grate a few carrots and cook in the broth.
Add uncooked rice and cook until done.
When rice is cooked, add chicken and serve.
Water may be added if needed.

title: waffles
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Sift and measure the flour.
Sift the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together.
Separate the egg yolks from the whites.
Beat the yolks, add the milk and mix together.
Add the melted shortening after it has cooled slightly.
Add the liquid ingredients to the sifted dry ingredients.
Mix only until the dry ingredients are blended.
Beat the egg whites until they are stiff.
Then fold them into the batter.
Pour the batter, about 1/3 cup (the amount varies with the size of the iron), on a hot waffle iron.
Bake about 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: pennsylvania corn soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook the pepper and onion in oil and butter until tender.
Stir in the flour and continue stirring over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add milk slowly, stirring after each addition to prevent lumping.
Set aside.
Place 1 cup corn, cream and tamari in blender.
Process on medium speed until fairly smooth.
Add corn/cream mixture and remaining corn to the milk mixture.
Heat thoroughly and serve topped with a dash of nutmeg and garnish with parsley.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Brown beef in pan.
Season to taste with garlic powder, buttery flavored salt and pepper.
Add tomato paste and whole tomatoes; mash or cut in small pieces.
Season with basil and oregano.
Let simmer over low heat about 2 hours.
If sauce becomes too thick, add water.

title: white cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch layer pans. Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until stiff and glossy.
Set aside.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Chop tomatoes, cabbage, onions and peppers.
Combine all ingredients until tender.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: butter sticks
directions: Melt margarine in a 7 x 14-inch pan.
Sprinkle in garlic powder.
Mix flour, sugar and milk as for biscuits.
Pat or roll about 1/2-inch.
Cut into strips.
Roll in melted margarine. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake in hot oven until brown, about 15 minutes.

title: jello buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice, sugar and Jell-O together to melt Jell-O; let cool and add buttermilk and stir well and refrigerate until thick.
Stir in Cool Whip, nuts and shredded apple. Refrigerate.

title: thelma daine's cool as a cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve and cool Jell-O in hot water.
Grind and drain cucumber and onion.
Combine with last 4 ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook on stove, covered for 5 hours at 250°.

title: lighthouse raspberry cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of square pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Cream shortening, salt, vanilla and remaining 3/4 cup sugar and egg yolks.
Beat until creamy.
Combine flour and baking powder in separate bowl.
Add alternately with milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Coat raspberries lightly with flour.
Add berries to dough.
(Save 1/3 cup of berries to sprinkle on top.)
Put in pan.
Sprinkle top with 1/3 cup of raspberries and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Do not underbake.

title: dream pie
directions: In large bowl, mix together Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice. Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crumb pie shells.

title: diet chicken-trout-turkey salad
directions: Yields 3 servings.
Each serving = 3 1/2 ounces protein.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Cut pineapple in small pieces.
Add marshmallows to pineapple chunks.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cook pineapple juice, sugar, egg, flour and vinegar until thick.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Next morning, add Cool Whip and pineapple and marshmallow mixture together with pineapple juice mixture with apples and peanuts.

title: italian beef
directions: Place raw roast in crock-pot.
Sprinkle dressing mix evenly over the top.
Cover and cook on low for 12 hours.
If you wish to slice the beef, refrigerate the cooked roast for 4 hours, slice and return to juice in the crock-pot.
If desired, you can shred the cooked meat and leave in the juices.
This is so easy and always turns out delicious.
Serve on buns.

title: family favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients (I use a food processor) and shape into loaf.
Spray loaf pan lightly with Pam and place meat loaf in pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: four-layer delight
directions: Melt oleo; put in flour and nuts to make a crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake crust at 350° until done.
Cool completely.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Use leftover ham.
Grease round casserole.
Put a layer of potatoes, then layer of onions.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Put a layer of sliced ham.
Dot with butter.
Repeat layers.
Finish with potatoes on top and dot with butter.
Add milk until bowl is half full.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until well browned and bubbly.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir to dissolve.
Add pineapple and stir.
Put half of mixture in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: a child's delight hopscotch breakfast
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread each slice of toast with 2 teaspoons strawberry preserves.
Top each with 1 slice of cheese, 3 slices of egg and 2 slices of bacon.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour beef - potato dumplings
directions: Boil first 7 ingredients until meat is tender.
Add last 2 ingredients to meat and cook over low heat until thick.
Serve with Potato Dumplings.

title: fruit tea sandwiches
directions: Beat butter and sugar at high speed with electric mixture until creamy.
Add flour and salt, mixing well.
Add almond extract and eggs.
Beat at medium speed for 10 minutes.
(Necessary to get proper texture.)
Spoon batter into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Cut cake with a 2-inch heart shaped cutter.
Spread 2 teaspoons preserves on half the hearts.
Cover with remaining hearts. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and top with mandarin orange sections. Yield:
16 to 18 sandwiches.

title: diabetic strawberry shortcake(calories: 153)
directions: Split the biscuit.
Slice the strawberries or mash according to desire.
Place the strawberries on the underside of the biscuit, cover and place the top on.
Cover with remaining strawberries. Beat the cream and top the dessert.

title: spinach dip
directions: Put in blender and blend thoroughly.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Mash them, adding milk, butter and garlic powder.
Then add sour cream and cream cheese.
You can refrigerate the potatoes and heat them up the next day, or use them on the day they are prepared.

title: almond loaf cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix cream cheese and butter thoroughly with a mixer.
Gradually blend in sugar, then begin adding eggs, one at a time, alternating with flour until all are used.
Add vanilla and almond flavoring.
Turn into a greased and lightly floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: audrey's tea cake cookies
directions: Put first five ingredients
in
large
mixing
bowl and cream well.
Add next four ingredients and cream until smooth. Batter may be separated into thirds.
Add pecans to one-third, peanut butter
chips to
one-third
and
chocolate
chips
to one-third. This
makes
variety
of
cookies.
However,
the cookies are very good plain.
Drop by spoonful, about the size of large walnut, onto greased cookie
sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Store in tight container.

title: good pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice until thick.
Add fruit, Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with red cherries.
Chill and serve.

title: milk chocolate fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Combine 4 cups sugar and 1 can evaporated milk and bring to a full rolling boil. Boil 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Pour half of this cooked mixture over the first mixture.
Fold in until chocolate is melted. Add remaining cooked mixture and mix thoroughly.
Let stand a few minutes then add 2 teaspoons vanilla and at least 1 cup of nuts if desired.
Pour into greased pan; cool and cut.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Allow sherbet to soften in punch bowl and pour ginger ale over it. Mix well and serve.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix with powdered sugar and margarine. Press 2/3 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix jello and water and let it barely jell.
Whip Milnot until stiff.
Add cream cheese and jello to Milnot and beat again, adding sugar, beating constantly.
Pour into pan and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top. Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Place butter slices, salt and pepper on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Debone chicken, placing it in a large casserole dish.
Blend soup and water; pour over chicken.
Place biscuits on top.
Return to oven and bake at 400° until biscuits are brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Dredge in
flour.
Put
about 1-inch of oil in skillet and brown chicken.
When	chicken
is brown, put in a baking
dish
or
pan.
Pour 1 small bottle of Kraft original barbecue
sauce over chicken.
Add enough water to cover chicken. Cover
with
foil and bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: shrimp over rice
directions: Saute onions after cutting into rings.
Add soup and heat slowly.
Add other ingredients; thin with pea juice.
Add chopped hard-boiled eggs and serve over rice.

title: gram worsley's pie crust
directions: *Can use Crisco but not as good.
Lard makes it delicious.

title: four layer chocolate pie
directions: Mix together the margarine, flour and nuts.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes a thin
crust. Bake for 15 minutes at 325° and cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add zucchini and mix.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Fold into egg mixture.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve over cream cheese or with a baked ham.

title: mini meat loaves and vegetables
directions: Combine meat, salt, egg, 1/2 can tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and 1/2 can French onions.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, form 3 mini loaves.
Place potatoes around loaves.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 35 minutes.
Place vegetables around loaves.
Stir to combine with potatoes.
Lightly season with salt and pepper.
If desired, top meat loaves with remaining tomato sauce.

title: angie's vegetable stew
directions: Saute onions; add potatoes and tomatoes.
Cook until tender. Add okra and cook until done.
Serve as a side dish.

title: chicken elegante
directions: Mix all ingredients (except stuffing) and place in a casserole.
Prepare stuffing according to package directions except use 2 cups of water.
Spoon over chicken and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dirt pudding dessert
directions: Blend everything except cookies together.
Crush cookies. Layer cookies and cream mixture in a flower pot (plastic or new clay pot without hole), starting and ending with cookies.
Chill. Can put flowers in pot and serve with new clean garden trowel. For extra fun, garnish with gummy worms.
Delicious and fun.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute pepper and onion with butter.
Remove from heat; add soups, Ro-Tel and milk.
Butter bottom of baking dish.
Add half bag of chips, chicken and all of cheese except 1/3 cup.
Pour mixture on top of chicken, then last of cheese and chips.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked apple
directions: Carefully core each apple by cutting a cone with a paring knife from top to bottom of the fruit.
Arrange the apples in a single layer in a glass baking dish which has been lightly buttered and dusted with brown sugar.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Stir in oil.
Mix noodles and marshmallows in large bowl.
Mix butterscotch, noodles and marshmallows until blended.
Drop on wax paper.
Let cool until set.
Can use sweet chocolate chips.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Let come to a bubbling boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Mix with apples.
Add Cool Whip to the top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: jenny link's beef picadillo dip
directions: In skillet, brown meat; drain off any fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press into buttered spring-form pan.

title: roast beef casserole
directions: Cook celery, onion and pepper in margarine until tender.
Add roast beef and cook several minutes.
Stir in soup, water, salt, soy sauce and Tabasco.
Place in casserole and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: apple butter
directions: *Use at least 1/3 Red Delicious apples.

title: crescent roll casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 package crescent rolls; just unroll and lay flat in pan.
Mix hamburger with rest of ingredients, except other can of rolls.
Cover rolls with hamburger mixture, then cover with remaining package of crescent rolls.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: kottbollar(swedish meatballs)
directions: Mix ground beef and pork well.
Beat milk and eggs together and pour over bread crumbs.
When soft, mix with meat and work well together.
Add spices and onion.
Work all together until light and fluffy.
Form into small balls (size of a walnut) and brown in deep fat, turning them as they brown.
A little hot water may be added while simmering.
Makes 90 small balls.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Mince garlic.
Shell and devein shrimp, removing tails also. In a large frying pan, melt butter in the oil over medium-high heat.
Add garlic; cook for about 30 to 45 seconds.
Add shrimp; cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, pepper, lemon juice and parsley; toss until shrimp are thoroughly coated.
Serve immediately over prepared vermicelli.
Makes 6 servings.

title: date-nut cookies
directions: Combine pecans, dates, cherries and 1/4 cup flour, tossing well.
Cream oleo; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk, ending with flour.
Stir in fruit mixture.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or lightly browned.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients, pour it into graham cracker pie crust.
Chill for 1 hour in the refrigerator.

title: chicken foster
directions: Place chicken pieces in a greased baking dish.
Lay a piece of cheese over each breast.
Warm together the soup and milk until smooth and pour over the chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle the stuffing mix over all.
Melt the butter and pour over the stuffing.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: Heat fat or oil to 375° in deep fat fryer or kettle.
Measure 1 1/2 cups flour and the remaining ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour.
Turn dough onto floured board.
Gently roll dough 3/8-inch thick; cut with floured cutter.

title: no-bake peanut oat cookies
directions: In medium saucepan mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add milk and butter.
Put over medium heat and bring to a boil.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and oatmeal. Drop by teaspoons onto foil.
Let stand until firm and cold.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: easy beef bourguignonne
directions: Combine meat and vegetables in a large casserole.
Mix together seasonings, flour, sugar and salt.
Sprinkle over.
Pour wine and broth over all.
Cover and bake for 4 hours at 325°.

title: instant spice tea mix
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Spoon into jars and seal.
To serve, add 2 teaspoons of tea mixture to a cup of hot water.
Great for us kids to make! Yield:
40 cups.

title: corn and dill muffins
directions: In a bowl, mix together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a small bowl whisk together milk, egg, corn kernels and melted butter until blended.
Add to dry ingredients, along with dill, and stir until blended.
Spoon into buttered muffin tin, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until toothpick inserted in muffin comes out clean (about 15 minutes).
Cool for 3 minutes, then remove.
Makes 15 muffins.

title: pepsi roast
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Pour over roast in large roasting pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 4 hours, turning after 1 1/2 hours.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: With a fork mix together flour, Crisco, salt, sugar and vinegar.
In a separate bowl beat egg and water.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with a fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Then with hands mold into a ball.
Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling. Dough can be left in refrigerator up to 3 days.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook frozen beans as directed on package.
Drain canned green beans, but do not cook.
Combine beans with soup.
Put into a 1-quart buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until bubbly.
Top with onions during the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: stack-a-biscuit stroganoff
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Brown ground beef, drain.
Mix into 2 1/2 to 3 quart casserole.
Ground beef, mushrooms and onions.
In medium saucepan, heat mushroom soup until bubbly, stir in 1/2 cup of sour cream.
Pour over meat mixture.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries. Heat (do not boil) juice. Remove from heat. Dissolve strawberry and cherry Jell-Os in juice, then melt cream cheese with fork. Add pineapple, cherries, cream cheese, pecans and Coke. Chill in refrigerator for about 1 hour.

title: peanut chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until golden brown at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix together and store in fridge, covered. Wait at least 10 hours before eating.

title: chicken supreme
directions: First, cut dried beef into small pieces and sprinkle into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Next, wrap the chicken breasts with a strip of bacon.
In a bowl, mix the sour cream and the cream of mushroom soup together.
Place your chicken breasts in the casserole dish; pour the soup mixture over the chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken stuff
directions: Mix soups together to gravy consistency.
Layer chicken, stuffing and soup, ending in soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ketchup
directions: *Oils can be bought in drugstore.

title: smoked oyster log
directions: Mix all but chives with a fork or mixer until well blended. Chill.
Shape into a log and sprinkle with chives or parsley. Chill until served with crackers.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Chop fruits and nuts and mix with orange and grape juice. Line a crock or casserole with brown paper and insert two strips of cloth in crock to facilitate removing and pack very closely. This should stand in a cool place about ten days before cutting.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello and black cherry jello with hot water. Let cool, then add Coke.
When mixture begins to thicken, add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate and allow to congeal.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Mix together and bake in pie plate in a 350° oven.
Serve with ice cream, whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Is also good plain.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover and cook 4 weeks at 465°.

title: tator tot casserole
directions: Salt hamburger and brown under broiler.
Drain fat off.
Add mushroom soup to pan and return to broiler and heat.
Add corn & green beans to pan and return to broiler and heat.
Just before eating add frozen tator tots to top of pan.
Return to broiler and heat until hot and brown.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all the above together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake approximately 1 hour or less until done.
Very good dish for potluck dinners.
Serves 8.

title: state fair sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter and oil with sugars; add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Measure by rounded teaspoonfuls; dip in colored sugar.
Put on cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake in a 375° oven for 9 minutes.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in the warm water.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, salt, cooking oil and soda to buttermilk.
Add yeast mixture.
Add flour to make soft dough and knead on floured board until smooth.
Cover with cloth and let rest 15 minutes.
Shape as desired.
Put in a greased pan in a warm place 1 1/2 hours or until doubled.
Bake at 375°.
Brush with butter and serve.
Dough will keep several days in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen rolls.

title: gelatin party layers
directions: In a bowl, prepare gelatin with water according to package directions; pour half into 2 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Stir in bananas; chill until set.
Chill remaining gelatin until it starts to set.
Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and walnuts; spread evenly over firm layer of gelatin in casserole.
Blend whipped topping into partially set gelatin until smooth and creamy; spoon over cream cheese layer.
Chill until set.
Garnish with additional whipped topping, strawberries and mint leaves if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheesy rice and beans
directions: In a large saucepan, mix all ingredients together.
Stir and cook over low heat until mixture is hot and cheese is melted.

title: scholl sweet and sour picnic beans
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp. Remove from pan. Drain on paper toweling, then crumble and set aside. Separate onion slices into rings and cook in bacon drippings until tender, but not browned. Stir in sugar, mustard, Tabasco sauce, garlic powder, salt and vinegar. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Precook rice and let cool in refrigerator overnight if possible.
Dice cooked shrimp.
Slice mushrooms.
Slice scallions. Beat eggs. Break up and separate rice.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix together and chill dough approximately 10 minutes.
Roll into balls, about 1 teaspoon.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: crusty white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, oil and 3 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough of the remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes. Place in greased bowl.
Brush top with salad oil.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 45 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese, spaghetti sauce and eggs together. Layer in 9 x 13 pan in the following order: uncooked noodles, 1/2 the sauce mixture, 1/2 the ground beef, package of Cheddar cheese, uncooked noodles, 1/2 sauce mixture, 1/2 ground beef and package of Mozzarella. Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Chop onion, set aside.
Prepare minute rice per package directions.
Add onion, tomato paste, and tomato sauce to ground beef.
Simmer and mix over low heat.
Pour ground beef into large bowl and mix with rice.
Add 1/4 can Italian stewed tomatoes and mix together.
If mixture is too dry, add more stewed tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Wash and cut 1/4 inch cap off of peppers.
Clean out peppers and save cap.
Fill each pepper with rice mix.
Put peppers in large baking dish, add leftover rice mix.
Pour remaining Italian stewed tomatoes over peppers and rice.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour or until peppers are soft.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Put onions and hamburg together and fry until brown, stirring frequently.
Add all remaining ingredients; simmer for 1 hour on low heat.
Serves 20.

title: aunt harriet's taboulie
directions: Soak bulgur with water for 1 hour.
Cut in scallions, tomatoes and parsley.
Refrigerate before serving to allow wheat to absorb moisture.

title: one minute cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to boil for 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter (I use crunchy), quick oats and vanilla.
Add nuts, if desired.
If you use crunchy peanut butter, you do not need nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheet.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Let the first 4 ingredients stand overnight. Wash off salt and drain well. Add the remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes. Place in canning jars.
Place in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry sour cream jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of mixture in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; mix. Add mayonnaise, water, and vanilla; mix until smooth. Bake in 2 (9 inch) pans that have been greased and floured. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: chinese style chicken wings
directions: Mix sugars together and add soy sauce.
Coat chicken with the sauce.
Bake at 350°, covered with foil, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, then bake another 15 minutes without foil.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Combine last 7 dressing ingredients.
Pour over salad; toss. Chill 8 hours.

title: italian calzone sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, cook sausage, onion and bell pepper until sausage is no longer pink; drain well.
Stir in mushrooms.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles, firmly press perforations to seal.
On ungreased cookie sheet, press or roll each into a 7 x 5-inch rectangle.
Spoon 1/4 of meat mixture on half of each rectangle.
Sprinkle cheese over meat mixture.
Fold remaining side over cheese, turnover fashion.
Press edges firmly to seal.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and melted butter. Place pecans in bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Add filling.
Bake slowly in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
If your oven is real hot bake at 325°.

title: squash marshmallow-pecan squares
directions: Wash and halve squash; discard seeds and fiber.
