Place squash, cut side up in 12 x 7 x 2-inch or 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine cracker crumbs, pecans, butter, sugar and nutmeg.
Brush squash with remaining butter.
Spoon 2 tablespoons nut mixture into each half.
Bake covered at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes until tender. Uncover.
Top each half with 1/4 cup marshmallows.
Bake 5 minutes or until marshmallows are puffed and golden.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; blend in eggs.
Add dry ingredients to butter, sugar and egg mixture alternately with pumpkin.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (depending on size of your pan).

title: easter candy
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Form into Easter eggs. Place on foil lined sheet pan and refrigerate for an hour.
Melt chocolate chips and was together.
Dip the eggs into the chocolate mixture and cool again. I use two forks to dip with.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump crushed pineapple into 9 x 13-inch pan and spread evenly (do not drain).
Dump pie filling; spread evenly on pineapple. Dump cake mix evenly over pie filling.
Slice margarine into pats and place evenly over cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans or coconut over mix.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Top will be crunchy and firm when done.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain first 4 ingredients well.
Mix them with the next 4 ingredients.
Top with a sauce made of the last 5 ingredients. Sauce should be mixed in a saucepan, brought to a boil and let cool.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate (9 x 1 1/4-inch). Combine and beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over low heat.
Stir in Karo syrup, water, vanilla, sugar and milk.
Fold in marshmallows. Spread in greased 8-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours.

title: scalloped cabbage and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put cabbage in saucepan; sprinkle with a few tablespoons of boiling salted water.
Cover; simmer over medium heat for 8 minutes. Drain well.
In mixing bowl, blend cheese, flour, salt and pepper.

title: easy drop biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine yogurt, egg substitute and oil.
Add liquid to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: microwave angel food cake
directions: Follow package directions for cake mix.
Put 1/2 to 2/3 cake batter in microwave Bundt pan.
Smooth top of cake batter. Microwave 4 minutes on High, then 2 minutes on Medium.
Cool 3 to 5 minutes, then invert onto plate, using spatula to remove edge and around cone.
Serve with strawberries and Cool Whip.
(Discard extra 1/3 batter or make small cake.)

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers thinly and soak in lightly salted water until crisp; drain.
Mix with sour cream or mayonnaise, chopped onion, vinegar and salt and pepper to taste.
Add chopped chives or parsley.
Keeps in refrigerator for several days.

title: microwave spanish rice
directions: In 2-quart glass dish, combine all ingredients.
Cover. Microwave on High for 12 minutes.*
Stir.
Microwave, covered, on High another 12 minutes.*
Let sit 5 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: fried tomato sandwiches
directions: Butter each side of bread.
Combine cream cheese, Miracle Whip, chives and dill weed; mix until smooth and put thickly on 4 buttered slices.
Top with tomato slices which should be large enough to fit bread and put remaining bread on top.
Press down slightly.
Dip sandwiches in mixture of eggs, milk, salt and pepper then fry in butter.

title: individual quiche casseroles
directions: Cook sausage links until brown; drain.
Reserve 2.
Slice remainder.
Cook mushrooms, celery and onion in butter until tender.
Beat together the eggs, flour, salt and paprika.
Add vegetables, sliced sausage links and cheese.
Pour 3/4 cup mixture into 4 individual baking dishes.
Halve remaining sausage links lengthwise.
Place one on each casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mrs. way's chewy bars
directions: Mix together in order listed.
Grease pan.
Cook 25 minutes at 325°.

title: pork chops with spinach dumplings
directions: Brown chops in hot fat in skillet; remove and keep warm.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of fat; saute onion and garlic until soft.
Add tomato juice, mushrooms, thyme, marjoram, rosemary, sugar, salt and pepper; mix well.
Return chops to skillet. Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Combine cooked spinach, bread crumbs, salt, egg, butter and cheese.
Place a mound of spinach mixture on each chop.
Cover; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with additional cheese, if desired.

title: creme brulee(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix yolks and sugar until blended (approximately 1 minute) in metal bowl.
In small saucepan, heat up cream and vanilla to approximately 180°.
Do not boil.
When cream mixture is hot, slowly add to yolk mixture until all the cream is in bowl.
Blend together.
Put mixture into creme brulee ramekens with water bath. Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until firm.
If you like, add your favorite berry.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine oil, sugar, pumpkin, eggs and cinnamon. Blend well. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda. Add to first mixture and blend well. Pour into greased jelly roll pan. Bake 25 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed with an electric beater until light and fluffy (4 to 5 minutes). Sift flour, cream of tartar, baking powder and salt together.
Add dry mixture alternately with milk and orange juice, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just to blend after each addition.
Stir in orange rind and flavorings.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan.
Remove cake from pan to a wire rack and cool completely.

title: crunchy chicken bake
directions: Wash and dry chicken well.
Blend egg and milk.
Mix potato flakes and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken in egg and then in potato/cheese mixture, coating thoroughly.
Melt butter in baking dish or low Pyrex dish.
Arrange chicken pieces skin side down in pan and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake uncovered in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; sprinkle with salt and pepper and remaining potato/cheese mixture.
Bake 30 minutes more.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix vegetables together.
In a small bowl blend sour cream, mayonnaise and ranch dressing together.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix well.
Freeze in Cool Whip containers.
Let thaw 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Add 1 small bottle of ginger ale per container.

title: corny corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in hot skillet.
Cook at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour gradually.
Mix well.
Then add potato chips.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar over before serving (optional).

title: apple salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Mix mayo, sugar and lemon juice. Add milk, marshmallows and Cool Whip. Add other mixture and chill.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze thawed spinach until well drained.
Mix well with remaining ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with chunks of French bread or raw vegetables.
Makes 4 cups.

title: lemon pie
directions: Bake
and
cool
graham
cracker
pie shell.
Beat 3 egg yolks and
add 1/2 cup lemon juice, then condensed milk.
Pour into pie
shell.
Beat
egg
whites with 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar and slowly add 1/4 cup sugar.
Add to top of pie.
Bake at
350° for
12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Vanilla wafers may be substituted for pie shell.

title: pimento and cheese
directions: Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: peach melba parfait
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup hot water in bowl.
Add unthawed raspberries.
Stir occasionally to separate berries.
Let thaw (it will begin to set).
In another bowl, pour 1 cup hot water over peach gelatin; stir to dissolve.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Add ice cream in 8 chunks; stir to melt.
Refrigerate until thick enough to mound.
Spoon lightly thickened raspberry mixture into 8 dessert dishes or parfait glasses.
When ice cream mixture has thickened, fold in peaches and spoon over raspberry mixture.
May put dollop of Cool Whip or whipped cream on top. Chill.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Heat olive oil and cook onion and pepper until soft.
Add tomatoes, paste, water, salt, pepper, oregano, garlic and red pepper.
Simmer on low for 3 hours.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg and molasses; mix well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and spices; mix well.
Add about 1/4 of dry mixture at a time to creamed mixture, mixing until smooth after each addition.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Shape dough into pinch balls and roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
(Tops will crack.)
Cool on wire racks.
Yield: 4 1/2 dozen.

title: cheap cake
directions: Makes 2 layers.
Mix and bake in moderate oven.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Melt butter.
Beat eggs.
Combine sugars and flour.
Add to butter and eggs.
Stir in milk and vanilla, then add pecans.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: poppy seed torte
directions: Melt
oleo; combine flour, sugar, nuts and oleo.
Blend well and
press	in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Cool well.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine wheat germ, cheese and seasonings. Dip chicken pieces in milk. Coat in dry ingredients. Place in 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish. Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a fork. Makes 4 servings.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl. Add sugar, salt, milk and vanilla; beat well. Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until well set.

title: vegetable stuffed potatoes
directions: In large skillet, over medium heat, cook carrots, pepper, and Italian seasonings in margarine until vegetables are tender-crisp. Add zucchini, cook until tender, about 1 minute more.
Slit potatoes lengthwise and push ends to center to open.
Divide and spoon vegetable mixture into each potato.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings 255 calories; 6 grams fat; 142 mg. sodium per serving.

title: caramel corn(oven baked)
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, salt and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes on low heat.
Add vanilla, soda and butter flavoring.
Stir quickly and immediately pour over popcorn and nuts.
Spread in large baking pans (greased).
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir frequently and watch it!

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Melt jelly in saucepan.
Add mustard; stir well.
Cut wieners in small pieces.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Drain; add to sauce.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish (9 x 13-inch) or smaller.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, depending on size and thickness of dish.
Serve hot.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken parts.
Spread catsup over chicken parts.
Place chicken in frying pan.
Pour Coca-Cola over chicken. Cover and cook slowly for about 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook another 30 minutes or after the first 45 minutes it may be put in baking dish in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Don't knock it until you've tried it.
You'll be surprised.
Serves 6.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Slice and cook carrots until tender; drain.
Melt margarine and cheese together.
Pour over carrots.
Sprinkle crumbled crackers over carrots and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: what cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and butter which has been broken into chunks.
Stir until butter is melted.
Sift flour with soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to oat mixture; mix well.
Add sugars and eggs; mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in preheated 375° oven about 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Top with Broiled-On Topping.
Serves 10.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Place all, except buttered bread crumbs, into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix well.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbly.

title: oatmeal spice cookies
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients, add remaining dry ingredients, add milk, and walnuts.
Form in balls. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Place bread cubes in a 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon, salt and raisins over bread.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325° or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool slightly and serve.

title: ground beef salami
directions: Blend thoroughly.
Form into two 9-inch rolls.
Wrap in foil (shiny side out).
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Poke holes in bottom of package (3 or 4) and place on broiler rack.
Put in oven and bake at 325° for 90 minutes.
Unwrap and cool.
Wrap in plastic wrap and store.

title: butterscotch pull-apart rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Spread nuts, top with rolls and cover with mixture of cinnamon, butter, sugar and pudding mix.
Cover with a towel; let rise overnight.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 24 hour cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Alternate flour and whipping cream until all is mixed together. Add vanilla; pour into well-greased tube pan (floured).
Bake for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and moist ingredients separately.
Mix together and blend well.
Oil glass baking dish, wipe out.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks and milk and add to dry ingredients.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add vanilla. Pour into deep dish baked pie crust.

title: marie's holiday drink
directions: Mix all together.
Freeze into slush or serve over ice in tall glass.
Garnish with lemon slice and cherry on toothpick.

title: quick chocolate cookies
directions: Combine pudding and Bisquick mix in a bowl.
Cut in shortening; mixture should resemble coarse meal.
Stir in egg and milk; blend well.
Stir in coconut and orange peel.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 275° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Grease a 3 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except egg in a bowl; mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Brush top with egg.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: creamy roquefort whip
directions: Use blender and mix all ingredients until smooth.
Chill before serving.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine and bake 1 hour at 325° or until lightly brown and tests done.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add more mayonnaise, if needed. Refrigerate.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and cool spaghetti; add diced pineapple, marshmallows, diced mandarin oranges and grapes (cut in halves).

title: mango and shrimp salad
directions: Halve shrimp if large.
Cut large slice from each side of the mango pit, then cut off the remaining flesh.
Cut the large mango slices into strips.
Blanch snow peas in boiling water for 1 minute.
Drain.
Cook under cold running water.
If preferred, snow peas can be served raw in the salad.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Stir until completely mixed.
Add nuts and potato chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
(A good way to use up crumbled-up potato chips.)

title: chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a shallow 9-inch baking dish. Cook broccoli until almost tender, then drain.
Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, soup and 1/2 cup cheese for the sauce.
Arrange broccoli in baking dish and cover it with half of the sauce; add the chicken and the remaining sauce.
Sprinkle the other 1/2 of the cheese over the entire casserole.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: granny's light bread
directions: Mix together water, oil, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in a small amount of warm water.
Add to the first mixture.
Add flour. Let rise until double in bulk.
Work down and shape into loaves. Allow to rise a second time.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: crab balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make 1-inch balls or place in muffin pans.
Cook until brown in 350° oven.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Place cream cheese, soup and garlic in a double boiler and melt together.
When melted, add gelatin which has been softened in the stock or wine.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Refrigerate to partially gel.
When sides have set, beat again until lightly fluffed.
Mix rest of ingredients except shrimp and mayonnaise. Add this mix with shrimp and mayonnaise to gelatin mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into oiled molds.
Refrigerate overnight.
This recipe will make enough for 2 medium sized fish molds.
Turn mold out onto serving platter and serve with crackers.

title: south louisiana red beans
directions: Wash beans and cover in cold water and soak overnight.
Cook sausage and garlic until browned.
Add beans and water in which they have been soaked, then ham bone and more water to cover, bay leaf and red pepper to taste. Cook slowly for several hours. Serves 8.
Serve over rice.
Cornbread goes well with red beans. Remove bay leaf before serving.
tags: ham bone with generous amount meat

title: nutty fingers
directions: Blend butter, nuts and vanilla until smooth; add flour and sugar gradually.
When thoroughly blended, shape dough into small finger-shaped cookies, place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still hot.

title: dumplings
directions: Break egg in measuring cup and fill with canned milk.
Mix with flour to blend.
Roll real thin.
Secret is to set for hours before dropping in broth.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil together.
Add eggs; sift flour.
Add salt, cinnamon and soda.
Add carrots and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, butter, corn syrup, salt and milk in
saucepan.
Cook slowly until mixture reaches 240 degrees on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, marshmallow creme and vanilla.
Beat until thick and pour in 9x13 greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: creamy tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed, drain.
Mix noodles, tuna, soups, salt and pepper in a 2-quart casserole dish.
In a separate bowl, melt margarine or butter.
Mix bread crumbs and grated cheese with butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes.
You may have to cover for last 10 minutes if crumbs get too brown.

title: grilled venison roast
directions: Set venison roast on heavy duty foil.
Cook bacon until almost done.
Saute veggies in grease.
Lay bacon across the top of roast.
Cover with veggies.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Cook on top rack of grill on low setting for an hour.

title: cloud biscuits(yankee style)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine egg and milk, add to flour all at once.
Stir until dough follows fork around bowl.

title: cool cucumber salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine sour cream, ReaLemon, sugar, salt and dill weed; mix well.
Add cucumber and onion.
Cover; chill to blend flavors.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beating well after each additon.
Dissolve soda in sour cream.
Add jam.
Stir into butter mixture.
Add spices and salt to mix, beating well. Fold in flour.
Bake in 5 or 6 9 inch cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coke chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Melt oleo and roll chicken in it.
Mix catsup and Coca-Cola together.
Pour over chicken in heavy skillet or Dutch oven with steam cover.
Cook 1 hour or until tender. Cook on top of stove.

title: taco pie
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain off grease.
Stir in taco seasoning mix.
Spoon into pie plate.
In blender, put milk, Bisquick mix and eggs. Blend until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until center comes clean on knife.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake only until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with lettuce and tomato.
Dot with sour cream.
Cut and serve.

title: mexican party dip
directions: Chop tomatoes.
Combine tomatoes, sour cream, chiles and party dip mix.
Stir to blend.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with chips or fresh vegetables.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stop cooking when mixture has reached a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add oats, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat well until blended.
Spoon onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: breadsticks
directions: Mix yeast, water and sugar; set aside.
Measure flour and salt to mixing bowl.
Add yeast mixture.
Knead 3 minutes.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Roll into rectangle and cut into sticks widthwise.
Melt 1 cube butter and pour into large baking pan.
Roll dough strips in butter and place side by side on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, Italian seasoning and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can be sprinkled with cinnamon and sugar for a sweet taste.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix with sugar and slowly stir in milk to make batter.
Melt butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish. Pour batter over berries in dish and sprinkle cinnamon and lemon peel.
Serve hot with ice cream of whipped cream.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Beat egg and stir in buttermilk, brown sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until flour is dampened.
Batter will not be smooth.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: bug balls(not to be eaten)
directions: Mix and add enough water to form dough.
Shape into balls; place throughout the house in places frequented by bugs.
(Do not place where children see or get to them; very poisonous).

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place in 2-quart baking dish.
Stir cream of mushroom soup (undiluted) and milk together in a small bowl.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour this over the sliced potatoes. Dot with the margarine.
Bake until done in 300° oven.
This will be 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: key lime pie
directions: Chill ingredients.
Combine in order.
Add green food coloring.
Pour into chocolate crust.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixer bowl, combine flour, sugars and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Mix in walnuts.
Mix in margarine until crumbly.
Do not overmix.
Reserve 2 1/4 cups mixture for topping. To remaining mixture, add 1 egg; mix until dough forms.
Spread dough on bottom of ungreased 12 x 18-inch pan.
In mixer bowl, combine pumpkin, condensed milk, 3 eggs, 1 tablespoon cinnamon, allspice and salt; mix well.
Pour evenly over crust.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until set. Cool; chill.
Refrigerate unused portions.

title: onion-baked pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In small bowl, combine soup mix and bread crumbs. Dip chops in egg, then bread crumb mixture until evenly coated. In lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking or roasting pan, arrange chops. Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes or until done, turning once.

title: chewy chocolate peanut butter chip cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; gradually add to butter mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in chips.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix by hand.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.
May be baked in muffin pans or regular bread pan.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cake mix and flour.
Knead dough and put in greased bowl.
Let rise until double.
Divide dough in half and roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread with melted butter, brown sugar and nuts or raisins.
Roll as for jelly roll and into 1/2-inch slices.
Put butter and brown sugar in bottom of pans.
Place rolls on top of this and let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate.

title: best ever hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Store in airtight containers. Use all of it this winter.
Will taste "yucky" next season.

title: spinach salad with oranges
directions: In a large salad bowl, toss the spinach, oranges, mushrooms, and bacon; set aside.
In blender or food processor, combine the ketchup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, onion, salt and pepper; cover and process until smooth.
While processing, gradually add oil in a steady stream.
Serve with the salad. Serves 4-6.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Place in casserole dish with rice and consomme.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: john marzetti
directions: Brown onion and pepper in shortening.
Add corn, macaroni and sauce.
Brown ground beef; mix with macaroni.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix everything together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Butter 2 baking sheets, each 15 1/2 x 12-inch; keep warm. Combine baking soda, 1 teaspoon water and the vanilla; set aside.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients, add eggs, then milk. Slowly simmer till thick. Pour into cooled crust and top with meringue. Bake till top is brown at 350°.

title: cornbread salad
directions: To prepare Tex-Mex cornbread add 4 oz. can chopped green chiles and a pinch of sage to your favorite cornbread recipe or a prepared mix that yields a 9 inch pan of cornbread.
Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Set aside.
Place half of crumbled cornbread in the bottom of a serving bowl.
Top with half of beans. In a medium bowl, combine tomatoes, pepper and onions; layer half of this mixture over beans.
Layer half of the cheese, bacon, corn and reserved salad dressing mix.
Repeat layers using remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Mix before serving.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain, also drain tuna.
Mix all ingredients together and put into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or in microwave for 10 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Thoroughly mix together first 3 ingredients.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls and place in freezer until hard.
Melt chips and paraffin together in double boiler.
Using a toothpick, dip peanut butter ball into melted chocolate and paraffin; place on wax paper and dry.
The result should be two-tone, a brown center and chocolate "sides."

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Arrange chicken in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix egg, soup, margarine, squash, onion and crumbs together. Mix stuffing and margarine together.
Alternate layers of squash mixture and stuffing mixture in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: kids chocolate-chip cake
directions: Grease	and
flour
x
13-inch pan.	Preheat oven to 350°. Combine
first
five ingredients together.	Fill baking pan half full
with batter.	Sprinkle about 1/3 of chips over batter.
Fill pan
with remaining batter.
Sprinkle remaining chips over
the top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until sides of cake bake away from pan. Test with toothpick.

title: hot tomato and bacon pasta
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Pour off all grease except 1 tablespoon from skillet.
Add olive oil and onions.
Saute until wilted.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes, then add the bacon and serve over noodles.

title: crab salad
directions: Cut crab meat in small pieces and combine with remaining ingredients (except cucumber).
Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving; add cucumber.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased and floured pan 8 x 8-inches.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pineapple-carrot molded salad
directions: Drain the pineapple; add enough water to the juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Heat to a boil; add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened; add pineapple and carrots.
Whip the cream until stiff.
Fold into jello mixture.
Pour into ring mold (1 1/2-quart size).
Chill until firm.
Best made a day ahead.

title: homemade grape-nuts
directions: Put in cake pans.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Put through screen and place in oven at 200° to 225° until dry.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Saute sausage, onions and pepper together in skillet; drain. Mix cornmeal and flour in a large bowl; add sausage, onion and pepper, corn, potato, cheese and eggs. Melt butter and pour into mixture. Stir well. Bake in a large iron skillet in a preheated 375° oven for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well.
Follow baking directions on cake mix box.
Frost with remaining strawberries and confectioners sugar.
Heat strawberry mixture.
Add sifted confectioners sugar until thick and smooth.

title: chicken soup with herbs
directions: Cook chicken with salt.
Remove skin and bones.
Put chicken pieces back in broth.
Add pimentos, celery, cabbage, peas and onion.
After ingredients are tender, add tomatoes and herbs. Re-heating has a tendency to make herbs stronger.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend baking soda, ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and butter.
Stir in sugar; beat in eggs.
Stir in molasses and add hot water.
Alternate with flour mix.
Pour in well-buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 45 minutes.

title: hot taco rice
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon cube.
Bring to a full boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: joe's grandmother's fruit cake
directions: Grandmother never told us how to mix this.
We just use our own way.
Cook in greased and floured angel food cake pan at 350° for 1 hour or longer.

title: curry chicken
directions: Wash chicken cut into 2 to 3 pieces.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and curry powder on chicken working seasoning into chicken.
Let stand covered overnight.

title: zucchini rectangle bars
directions: Mix together the eggs, butter, sour cream, yogurt, sugar, zucchini and syrup; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together. Combine mixtures.
Add nuts and mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Cool.
Cut into rectangles.
Dip in glaze and decorate.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Layer pieces of lettuce in airtight container.
Add layer of bacon, onion, then cauliflower.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Add dressing to top layer of salad.
Keep in refrigerator overnight in airtight container.
Just before serving, toss salad to blend ingredients.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Cream butter or margarine and 3 tablespoons 10x sugar until fluffy in medium-size bowl; stir in flour gradually, then pecans until well blended.
Chill several hours or until firm enough to handle.
Roll dough, a teaspoonful at a time, into marble-size balls between palms of hands; place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 20 minutes or until lightly golden.
Cool on cookie sheets 5 minutes; remove carefully.

Roll in 10x sugar in pie plate while still warm to make a generous white coating; cool completely on wire racks. Store with waxed paper or transparent wrap between layers in container with tight-fitting cover.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together flour, cocoa, salt, sugar and soda.
Add water and Miracle Whip; mix by hand.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheesecake supreme
directions: Mix all crust ingredients well, reserving 3 tablespoons of mixture.
Press remainder in bottom and 2 1/2 inches up sides of 9-inch pie plate.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple with pudding.
Stir in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare in one bowl brownies as directed using 4 eggs (no walnuts).
Spread in prepared pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, egg and flour in same bowl until well blended.
Spoon mixture over brownie batter, swirl with knife to marbleize.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: diabetic peach crumb bake
directions: Layer sliced peaches in bottom of 8 inch square baking dish coated with vegetable spray. Combine graham cracker crumbs, cinnamon and nutmeg in small bowl, stirring well. Add margarine, stir until combined. Sprinkle graham cracker crumb mixture over peaches. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm.

title: ginger snaps cookies
directions: In a large bowl combine about half of the flour, brown sugar, shortening, molasses, egg, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Beat with an electric mixer on medium to high speed till combined.
Beat or stir in remaining flour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in the granulated sugar to coat.
Place ball 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.

title: clams casino
directions: Open shells, letting clams remain in one half.
In medium frypan, saute bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, crumble and reserve.
Pour off excess fat, add onion and pepper and saute for 5 minutes.
In small bowl mix chives, cheese, paprika, pepper, seafood seasoning and m.s.g. together.
Blend into sauteed vegetables.
Add the reserved bacon.
Place 1 teaspoon of bacon mixture on each opened clam.
Place clams on shallow baking pan and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve with melted butter.
Makes 24.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: *If using all-purpose, add 1 tablespoon baking powder and 1 teaspoon salt.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease square pan (8 x 8-inch or iron skillet). I use Pam spray. In small bowl, blend ingredients. Pour into prepared pan and bake about 25 minutes.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix everything together in a large bowl and chill.

title: donut snow men
directions: With white icing, fasten two sizes powdered donuts together. Add donut hole for the head. Faces and buttons are made with Cake Mate gels. The chocolate covered cherry hat is attached with Cake Mate chocolate icing. Make arms with pretzels.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Saute onions, celery and mushrooms in butter.
In saucepan, combine broccoli, soup, cheese, lemon juice and sauteed vegetables.
Heat through and serve warm as a dip for raw vegetables or chips.

title: orange-coconut balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers to fine crumbs; add next 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Form into balls and roll each in flaked coconut; freeze.
Serve frozen.
Yield: About 4 dozen.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Split muffins.
Give each child a plate to make their pizza on.
Have ingredients in bowls and a spoon in pizza sauce.
Start with 2 teaspoons sauce (they put on) and let them add what they want, ending with cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven until cheese is bubbly, about 10 minutes.

title: sherbet
directions: Mash bananas, squeeze juice from oranges and lemons using some of the pulp.
Add sugar, milk and salt.
Freeze.
Add milk last.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a large bowl, combine the cheese, soup, sour cream, onion, green and red pepper, 1/4 cup of butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fold in the thawed hash browns.
Turn the mixture into the prepared dish.
Toss together the corn flakes and 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Sprinkle over the potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until the casserole is golden brown and the potatoes are tender.

title: reuben spread
directions: Chop the corned beef, Swiss cheese and sauerkraut. Add dressing; mix well.
Pour into Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Surround spread with the rye bread and serve hot.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in oleo until tender.
Add flour; cook until thickened, stirring often.
Add all ingredients. Place in long baking dish.
Bake at 325° until hot or lightly brown.

title: zucchini squash cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix with oil, sugar and eggs.
Stir in zucchini, nuts and vanilla. Pour in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda and baking powder. Set aside.
Melt chocolate in square pan.
Mix sugar and chocolate.
Add oleo next. Mix well. Add beaten eggs.
Mix all together.
Next add buttermilk. Add dry ingredients to mixture. Add vanilla.
Mix well. Cook in a sheet cake pan about 35 or 40 minutes until done at 350°.

title: mom's stew dumplings
directions: Mix as mixing biscuits.
It will be a soft, sticky dough. Drop in broth and cook 15 to 20 minutes; cover while cooking.

title: trio cheese ball
directions: Beat cheese in mixer bowl on medium speed until fluffy, scraping sides and bottom of bowl often.
Beat in onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in pecans.
Cover and chill 2 to 4 hours.
Mold cheese mixture into one large ball or 36 small balls (each about 1-inch in diameter).
Roll in parsley or can roll in chopped nuts.
Place on serving plate.
Cover and chill until firm (about 2 hours).

title: overnight company salad
directions: Place in layers in bowl.
Spread 1 cup Miracle Whip over ingredients and sprinkle 1 tablespoon brown sugar on top. Sprinkle on 2 to 4 ounces grated Cheddar cheese and 1/2 jar Bac*Os.
Let chill overnight.
Toss well before serving.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine crab meat, shrimp, mayonnaise, onion, celery, salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Pour into buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with potato chips.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 400° oven until thoroughly heated.
Serves 6.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cornflakes or potato chips. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put crushed corn flakes, or potato chips, over the top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Cook 45 minutes or until transparent.
Pack and seal in sterile jars.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in bacon drippings; place all ingredients except the bacon in a greased baking dish.
Mix well.
Top with strips of bacon.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry shrub
directions: Cook raspberries 10 minutes.
Rub through strainer with wooden spoon; cool.
Add concentrate; stir in ginger ale.
Serve immediately in tall glasses with ice cubes or crushed ice.
Makes 12 servings; 1 cup each.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in a buttered casserole dish at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: slice of the sun cookies(uncooked)
directions: Blend wafers, cut up orange slices and pecans.
Stir in the Eagle Brand milk.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Form in a log-like roll, then roll up in foil and chill.
Slice and serve.

title: fried chicken
directions: Roll chicken pieces in flour.
Place in fry skillet into melted butter and Crisco; cook until brown, then turn down on low and cook about 30 minutes.

title: veggie bars
directions: Line large ungreased pan, 11 x 17, with rolls. Bake at 350° for 7 or 8 minutes only until they start to brown. Do not overcook. Cool.

title: milan pineapple pie
directions: Beat whites until stiff, add sugar a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Fold crackers and nuts into egg white mixture.
Pour into 10-inch pie pan (preferably glass).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: fast fixing cake
directions: Pour small amount of oil in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan to grease.
Mix ingredients leaving 1/3 of chocolate chips to pour on top after mixing.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
(Peanut butter chips can be substitute for chocolate chips.)

title: country-style chicken
directions: Mix 1/2 teaspoon salt with flour.
Roll chicken in this. Brown chicken on both sides in skillet.
Peel potatoes, onions and carrots, cut up.
Cut green peppers.
Mix remaining salt, sugar and pepper with tomatoes.
Place about 1/3 of vegetables in bottom of pot.
Place chicken on top and rest of vegetables.
Pour tomatoes and water over all.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cook about 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In at least 1 1/2-quart bowl, mix peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook 8 minutes on High.
Stir after 4 minutes.
(Cook until hard-ball stage.)
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook 1 minute longer. Add baking soda and quickly stir until light and foamy.
Pour out on buttered baking sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put soup in casserole dish.
Mix in 1/2 soup can of milk.
Add beans and onion rings; mix in onion rings and lay a layer on top. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave, covered, for 8 minutes on High.

title: "lent" casserole
directions: Boil macaroni first.
Mix ingredients together.
This fills 2-quart casserole.
Put 1/2 stick butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into an ungreased 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Make 3 holes in this mixture.
Add vinegar in 1 hole, melted butter in 1 hole and vanilla in 1 hole.
Mix water and coffee together.
Blend everything together with fork.
Pop into oven and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stew
directions: Rinse meat; leave moist.
Dredge in flour.
Melt shortening and brown meat; makes thick gravy.
Put water to cover meat.
Add sauces (last 4 ingredients).
Cook slow until done, then add vegetables.
Cook until done.
Add can of peas at last.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine together over medium heat.
Add cocoa and stir.
Remove from heat.
Quickly add sugar and vanilla. Stir until blended.
Pour into pan and let sit for 1 hour before slicing.
This dish can be frozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute carrots, zucchini and onion until soft in pan sprayed with Pam.
Add mushroom soup, bread crumbs and sour cream.
Salt to taste and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or microwave 10 minutes. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, corn syrup and salt in large (2-quart) bowl.
Microwave on High until mixture begins to boil. Cook for 4 minutes, stirring 3 times.
Add baking soda and vanilla; stir.
Put the popped corn in unrecycled grocery sack. Pour mixture over corn and stir.
Cook for 1 1/2 minutes in microwave; shake sack hard.
Cook for 15 seconds.
Nuts may be added in the last 15 seconds.

title: miriam's marinated mushrooms
directions: Put all ingredients, except mushrooms, in large saucepan. Heat to boiling; simmer for 10 minutes, covered.
Add mushrooms. Simmer, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Transfer to bowl.
Chill. Before serving, drain the marinade, remove bay leaf and garlic. Serve cold or at room temperature.

title: hard candy
directions: Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310°.
Remove from heat. After boiling has stopped, stir in flavoring of your choice and food coloring.
Pour into lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break or cut into pieces.
Shake in bag of powdered sugar and store in Tupperware or airtight container.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add vanilla, flour, chips and pecans.
Mix well and chill.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 15 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and bake first 3 ingredients at 400° for 8 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fold Cool Whip into softened cream cheese and sugar.
Spread on cooled pretzel mixture.
Mix jello into 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
After strawberries have thawed, let stand 10 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate.

title: khoushaf(fresh fruit salad)
directions: Make a syrup by boiling together sugar and water; cool.
Peel, core and slice the apples.
Slice bananas after peeling.
Put the apples, bananas, pineapple and nuts into the syrup and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Just before serving, add strawberries and a few drops of orange blossom water for flavoring.
Mix carefully and spoon into sherbet glasses.
Garnish with a sprig of mint or an unhulled strawberry (optional).

title: mrs. chandler's potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in 1/8-inch slices.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, horseradish, celery seed and salt.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix parsley and onion.
In a large serving bowl, arrange layers of potatoes.
Salt lightly.
Cover with a layer of mayonnaise-sour cream mixture, then a layer of onion mixture. Continue layering, ending with parsley and onion.
Do not stir! Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving. The salad is better if it is made the day before.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into greased casserole dish.

title: mini pizza mix
directions: Grind ham, chop mushrooms and grate cheese.
Mix and add other ingredients, mixing well.
Spread on split English muffins and broil until bubbly.
Can be eaten this way or cut into wedges.
Mix well.
Refrigerate indefinitely or you can freeze.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice. Add water to juice to equal one cup, heat to boiling. Add gelatin, cranberry sauce, ginger ale, chopped nuts, cream cheese and pineapple. Put mixture in a one quart mold or casserole dish and congeal.

title: deluxe pineapple dessert
directions: Slice bananas in a 2-quart Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle pineapple chunks on top of bananas.
Mix water and cornstarch; pour over fruit.
Melt oleo, then add cornflakes, coconut and brown sugar. Mix well.
Pour over fruit and bake for 20 minutes or until hot at 375°.

title: beef brisket with sauerkraut
directions: Cover brisket with water; season and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Add sauerkraut, wine or vinegar and brown sugar.
Cook about 1 hour longer or until meat is tender.
Add grated potato and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: cherry mousse
directions: Soak the Grape Nuts cereal in the cherry juice.
Quarter the cherries.
Whip the cream.
When nearly stiff, whip in the powdered sugar.
Stir in the other ingredients.
Place in a shallow dish and freeze.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Put potatoes and onions in a 13 x 9 baking dish, add seasoning. Cut stick of butter and put slices of bacon on top.

title: coconut pineapple pies
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and melted butter; mix well.
Add pineapple and coconut, mixing well.
Pour into pie shells.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan.
Brown rice and onions in margarine, stirring frequently.
Pour beef broth, mushrooms, onions and browned rice in casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: kool orange delight
directions: Mix cottage cheese with orange jello, mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Add the fruit.

title: real italian tomato sauce
directions: Heat a large kettle over medium heat.
Put in the oil, onion, mushrooms, basil and garlic.
Cover and reduce the heat to medium-low.
Stir frequently; you may need to add a tablespoon or two of water to keep it from sticking.
When the onions are translucent, add the remaining ingredients, except the salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil on high heat; then reduce to simmer and let cook for an hour or so, stirring occasionally and breaking up the whole tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese in milk over low heat (I melt mine in my microwave).
Don't allow it to overheat, or your milk will curdle. Remove from heat and add Texas Pete, vinegar, Worcestershire and pimiento.
Stir well and pour into a covered container.
May store in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and
shortening.	Add
one egg at a time, mixing well
after each.	Sift all dry ingredients and add to mixture. Add
vanilla.
Bake
in tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour or until just done.	Check with toothpick.
Cool on rack.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Put broccoli and chicken broth in blender for 2 minutes on low.
Put in top of double boiler and add other ingredients, a little at a time.
Cook until very hot in double boiler.
Do not let boil.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Melt butter, add garlic in pan. Mix in flour, add milk, and both cheeses.
Cook med-low heat until cheeses are melted.
Should start to thicken a little, if not add some milk and flour mixture to pan.
Add pepper and nutmeg to taste.
Serve over noodles or fettuccine.

title: danish pastries
directions: Sprinkle yeast into very warm water in a 1-cup measure. (Water should feel comfortably warm when dropped on wrist.)
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon of the sugar.
Stir until yeast dissolves.
Let stand until bubbly and double in volume, about 10 minutes.

title: jello and cream cheese
directions: Make jello with nectar substituted for cold water.
Chill. Blend in softened cream cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Cover and store in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Fill muffin tins almost full (doesn't rise much).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Batter can be kept up to 6 weeks.
Do not mix as being used.
Just fill muffin tins as needed.
Very moist!

title: potato tomato bake
directions: In saucepan, blend dry sauce mix from potato mix with tomato sauce; add green pepper and 2 1/4 cups water.
Heat to boiling. Add potatoes; mix well.
Turn into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° until potatoes are tender, 30 minutes.
Top with onions; bake until onions are heated through, about 3 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: rum truffles
directions: Put the chocolate into a large heatproof bowl.
Add the coffee and cream.
Set the bowl over a pan of barely simmering water and leave until the chocolate has melted.
Stir the mixture occasionally.
Remove the bowl from the pan.
Using hand-held electric whisk, whisk the chocolate mixture for 10 to 15 minutes, until thick enough to stand in soft peaks.
Add the rum and whisk for a further 2 to 3 minutes.
Using a rubber spatula, scrape the mixture into a small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for about 1 1/2 hours or until firm but not solid.
Chill a baking tray.
Sift the cocoa over the chilled baking tray.
If the chocolate mixture is very stiff, work it with a wooden spoon until just softened.
Drop teaspoonfuls of the mixture onto the cocoa.
Lightly coat your fingertips, by pressing them into the cocoa.
Shape each heap into a ball between your fingertips, then roll in the cocoa until evenly coated and place in a petit fours paper case.
Continue making truffles in this way until all the mixture is used.
Chill for about 5 minutes to firm.
Pack in a pretty box with waxed paper between layers to prevent sticking.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and juice in hot water.
Chill until thickened.
Add cranberries, oranges, celery and nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Toast pecans in a 200° oven until warm.
Set aside.
Cook sugar, corn syrup and water to 240°, then add pecans.
Cook to 295°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and stir until dissolved.
Add soda and salt; stir vigorously.
Pour out in butter greased pans.
Spread as thinly as possible.
Break into pieces when cooled.

title: happy squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in blender.
Cut 1/4-inch slices of dough and line the bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan, ungreased.
Spread mixture over dough.
Cut second roll of dough as first in 1/4-inch slices and the top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Refrigerate a couple of hours or overnight before cutting.

title: basta pasta
directions: Melt oil and butter in skillet.
Add mushrooms and cook until soft.
Add Prosciutto, tomato, nutmeg, sage and cream.
Heat over medium-high heat 4 to 5 minutes until thick.
Pour sauce on cooked pasta.
Add Parmesan, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage by hand or in food processor.
Dice green onions.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil.
Mix in large bowl, with all ingredients, except noodles.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Before serving, add noodles and mix well.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: greek easter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Mix the first 5 ingredients together thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method (or by sifting).
Blend flour, baking powder and cloves; stir into butter mixture and mix well.
Shape dough in small balls, about 3/4-inch in diameter, or in cylindrical shapes, formed in 2-inch long half moons.
Place cookies on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, or until cookies are set, but not browned.
Let stand 2 minutes before removing from baking sheet.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar.
(For a more authentic Greek cookie, omit ground cloves and place a whole clove in center of
each cookie before baking.)
Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt candy bars over water.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Mix in candy bars and mix well.
Add flour and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
May need to bake a little longer.

title: sausage stir-fry
directions: Cook rice and keep warm.
Saute vegetables in oil until crisp and tender.
Add sausage and season to taste.
Heat thoroughly, mix in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and serve immediately over rice. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter; sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour canned milk evenly over crumbs. Top evenly with remaining ingredients and press down gently. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: stuffed hot dogs
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Using a greased and floured spring form pan, put 1/2 of the batter in the bottom of the pan.
Top with 1/2 of the filling mixture.
Repeat again until all ingredients are used.

title: caponata a la rosemary
directions: Saute eggplant, onion, pepper, celery and garlic in oil.
Add tomato sauce and paste; simmer for 10 minutes, then add olives and remaining ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Adjust spices to taste.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 400 degrees until golden.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom

title: orange sunshine cake
directions: Mix cake mix and jello.
Beat in eggs and water; add oil and pour into greased tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: low-fat delicious moist turkey meatballs(makes about 20)
directions: Combine all except the oil and form into little slightly flattened balls and quick saute them in the oil in a nonstick frypan on both sides until browned and half-cooked.
Put them on paper towels to blot up any excess oil.
Then plop them into your favorite spaghetti sauce or brown sauce or whatever sauce to finish cooking.
They're really good!

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese, then bacon bits over all.
Make 8 hours ahead.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add remaining ingredients.
Roll out to desired thickness.
Cut out in doughnut shapes and fry in hot Crisco oil.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for 9-inch one-crust pie as directed on package.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.
Cut butter into thin slices and place over top of pies (1/4 stick for each pie).
Bake in a preheated oven at 300° to 350° until done.

title: chocolate texas sheet cake
directions: Combine
flour, sugar and
salt.
Bring
water,
cocoa, margarine and oil to a boil for
minutes
and pour over the flour mixture.
Add remaining
ingredients to mixture and bake in sheet pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top the cake with glaze.

title: green goop
directions: Melt marshmallows and jello in 7 cups of boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Set aside to congeal.
Next day, at least 1 hour before ready to serve, whip jello with mixer.
Then add softened cream cheese.
Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Stir in whipped cream.

title: fish bowl jell-o
directions: Follow directions on box to make Jell-O.
Refrigerate partially.
When Jell-O is partially chilled, pour it into a clear bowl and blend gummi fish into the Jell-O mixture.
Mix the fish to look like they are swimming.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add vanilla and water, then flour. Add chopped pecans.
Chill awhile in refrigerator.
Roll in any shape.
Cook at 300 degrees until delicate brown, about 40 minutes.
Roll in sifted powdered sugar as you take them off the cookie sheet.

title: old fashioned irish stew
directions: Combine
flour,
salt,	pepper and glutamate in a bowl. Coat meat with flour mixture.
Melt butter; add meat, browned. Add water, celery and bay leaf. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and
simmer
for
hours or until meat is almost tender. Add remaining ingredients.	Continue cooking 1/2 hour or
until meat
and
vegetables
are	tender.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour together. Add water and cook until clear.
Add lemon juice, rind and butter. Add egg yolks and cook 2 minutes.
Put in baked pie shell.
Use egg whites for making meringue or whipped topping may be used.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion together.
Drain.
Add margarine; mix broccoli, soup, rice, 1/2 grated cheese, salt and pepper to taste. Pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit pie(no sugar)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except fruit.
Place fruit into an unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over fruit.
Bake 15 minutes at 425° and then 50 minutes at 350°.
Happy eating!

title: chocolate rum balls
directions: Melt chocolate over hot, not boiling water.
Combine marshmallow cream and rum flavoring.
Stir in chocolate; mix well. Add cereal, coconut and nuts.
Form into balls.
Roll in additional coconut or nuts, if desired.
Chill until firm.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: 7-up biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop on greased baking sheet. Cook until brown.

title: pecan crunch cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add crushed potato chips and nuts.
Stir in flour.
Form into balls about 1 teaspoon each. Press flat with bottom of small water glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350°
for 16 to 18 minutes until lightly browned.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken
in
foil
one
hour
at 350° and cut into pieces.
Save
cup
juice from chicken, add water to make 1 cup if
necessary.
Butter
9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer tortillas, chicken, onions and green chilies.
Then repeat a second time. Mix soups
with Pet milk and chicken juice.
Pour over chicken and etc.
Top
with
cups grated sharp Cheddar cheese. Let stand
24 hours in refrigerator.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Serves 8 to 12.

title: orange and onion salad
directions: Arrange lettuce leaves, onion and oranges on salad plates. Chill.
Just before serving, sprinkle with almonds.
Serve with poppy seed dressing.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add taco seasoning and onions. Mix together lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Just before serving, add hamburger, taco chips and dressing.
Toss well.

title: ruth's cookies
directions: Cream butter with white and brown sugar and the egg.
Combine the baking soda and salt with flour.
Add flour mixture alternately with oil.
To the butter mixture, add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.
Makes approximately 75 cookies.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel, seed and mash 1 ripe avocado.
Add picante sauce, lemon juice and salt.
Mix well.
Makes 1 cup.

title: macaroni and tuna salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni noodles.
Add drained tuna.
Mix with mayo and drained peas.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate-pecan chess pie
directions: Bake pie crust until light brown.
Stir together sugar and next eight ingredients.
Add eggs, stirring well.
Add pecans last.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in clear water until tender.
Peel while warm.
Mash with electric mixer on low speed.
Add butter or oleo while potatoes are still warm.
Add sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla. Beat well, but do not clean beater blades (this is where the strings are).
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until set and lightly brown.

title: sally jessy's stuffed french toast
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cut bread into cubes.
Spread half the bread into prepared pan.
Cut cheese into small cubes and sprinkle half over bread in the pan.
Repeat, layering with remaining bread and cheese.
Whisk the eggs, milk and syrup in large bowl.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 15 minutes. Serve warm with additional syrup.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Note: Add chocolate chips for variety.

title: sweet potatoes with cranberries(10 servings)
directions: Combine the first eight ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Stir yams into the mixture.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix boiled sweet potato, sugar, butter, eggs and flavor thoroughly.
After these ingredients are blended, add cake mix and mix for two to three minutes with mixer.
Put in two 9-inch cake pans or Bundt pan.
Make cupcakes also.
Heat oven to 350°. Grease or spray pans throughly.
Place cake in oven.
Cake will be done when toothpick comes out of cake dry.
(Icing optional.)

title: sweet nothings
directions: Melt margarine, butterscotch and peanut butter in a double boiler until melted.
Put 1/2 of the Chex cereal in large mixing bowl.
Pour peanut butter mixture over Chex.
Gradually stir with spatula until well coated and adding more Chex, until all of box is used and well coated.

title: chicken livers with rice
directions: Saute chicken livers in oil in a Dutch oven 5 minutes or until brown.
Remove livers and drain on paper towels; reserve skillet drippings.
Cut livers into quarters; set aside.
Saute carrots, onion, parsley and garlic in reserved drippings until onion is tender.
Add chicken livers and next 6 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in tomatoes and cook until thoroughly heated.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: bermuda pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Sprinkle brown sugar over top and lay onions over that.
Cover and simmer until done.
Oh, add 2 cups water, then cook until done.
Serve with rice.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: Combine first four ingredients and let stand for 20 minutes. Layer remaining ingredients in a large, deep casserole dish.
Pour liquid over layers.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 325° for five hours. Serves 6.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine and let stand overnight.

title: honey mustard dip
directions: Combine ingredients and blend well.
Chill before serving.

title: ham and egg stack
directions: Whip together first 5 ingredients.
Saute pepper and onion. Add spinach and nutmeg.
Cook 5/8 cup egg mixture in greased 10-inch skillet as for an omelet.
Slide or roll into greased 10-inch round quiche pan.
Layer 1/2 ham, 1/2 spinach, 1/2 cottage cheese and 1/2 Cheddar cheese on top.
Cook another omelet and repeat layers.
Cook a third omelet.
Slide on top of layers. Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375° until hot.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and 3 tablespoons of cocoa in a bowl.
Add milk, vegetable oil and vanilla extract.
Stir until blended.
Turn batter into an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: crazy pigs
directions: In Dutch oven or crock-pot, layer the hamburger, rice, tomato soup and cabbage.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Repeat this 4 or 5 times.
Top with can of stewing tomatoes and 2 cans of water.
Cook on top of stove on medium heat for 2 hours or in a crock-pot for 4 hours or until cabbage is tender.

title: salmon log
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients; chill.
Form into a log and roll in pecans and parsley flakes.

title: crock pot chicken
directions: Put chicken pieces into crockpot.
Add spaghetti sauce, oregano, garlic salt, or/and other favorite seasonings.
Put lid on pot and cook on low for 8 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add flour, eggs, Karo and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell and cover with pecans.
(I use chopped pecans and mix them into batter.) Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water, pour into blender.
Add cottage cheese, cream cheese and Equal; cover. Blend at medium speed, scrap sides occasionally, about 2 minutes, until mixture is smooth.
Pour into large bowl.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Divide into 8 dishes.
Using 1/2 can of lite cherry pie filling, top each dish with 1/8 of filling.
Yields 8 servings.

title: tangiers island corn pudding
directions: Blend corn and milk; add sugar.
Beat eggs and add to corn. Make paste of cornstarch; mix with corn mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut up lettuce in large bowl.
Add tomato.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain and cool.
Add to lettuce.
Drain chili beans and add to lettuce.
Add cheese.
Add taco sauce and Western dressing.
Mix together until well coated.
Add 1/2 of crushed chips and mix.
Top with remaining chips.

title: pickled vegetables
directions: Wash vegetables.
Dry and place in a big jar or crock with onions.
Bring water to a boil in a pot.
Add salt.
Let cool, then add pepper, garlic and bay leaves and pour over veggies.
The liquid should cover them.
If not, boil more water and add.
Cover jar with a cloth or cheesecloth and keep cool for 1 week in a dark place.

title: zucchini dressing
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole. Cook zucchini and onion in a little water until tender.
Put on top of margarine.
Mix stuffing as directed on box.
Put on top of onion and zucchini.
Layer in order:
chicken soup, sour cream and 1/2 stick melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fresh apple and orange bread
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt into a bowl.
Place butter or shortening, orange juice and eggs in blender container; blend well.
Add apples and orange.
Blend until fruit is chopped fine. Add raisins and nuts.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: braised beef
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine all ingredients in large Dutch oven or covered roasting pan.
Stir until well blended.
Bake 3 to 4 hours until meat is tender.
Cool.
Put into eight 1-pint freezer bags or containers.
Seal, label and freeze.
Use within 3 months.
To serve, heat thoroughly and pour over rice or buttered noodles.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Make cookie dough.
Put in oven 8 minutes.
Take out and eat.

title: artichoke rice salad(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Put Rice-A-Roni into bowl to cool.
Add onions and olives to rice.
Drain artichoke hearts into bowl.
Combine with marinade the curry powder and mayonnaise.
Add to rice mixture.
Mix well. Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
This can be made ahead of time and kept in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8-inch cake or pie pan. Combine in a large bowl, flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda, sugar and cardamon.
Add margarine and cut in with a pastry blender or knife until crumbly.
Beat egg slightly and mix with buttermilk; add to dry ingredients and stir until blended.

Turn out on a floured board and knead until smooth, 2 to 3 minutes. Divide dough in half; shape into a round loaf and place in pans. Press down until dough fills pans. With a sharp knife, cut crosses on tops of loaves about 1/2-inch deep.
Cut the crosses in the middle of loaves.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cold rice salad
directions: Combine in a bowl, rice, green onion, pepper, celery and olives.
In another bowl, beat the oil, wine vinegar and Dijon mustard.
Toss well, seasoning to taste.
Toss well.
Chill. Serves 4.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat and add peanut butter.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth and add oats.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and let cool.

title: fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in black iron skillet, except morsels, vanilla and nuts.
Bring mixture to a boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil mixture for 6 minutes.
Add morsels, vanilla and nuts to mixture.
Remove from heat and stir well. Pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Let cool, then cut.

title: mexican eggplant skillet
directions: Saute onion and beef; add tomato sauce, green pepper, oregano, chili powder and salt.
Simmer gently 15 to 20 minutes on low heat.
Slice eggplant (usually 1/3 to 3/4-inch thick).
Place eggplant on top of meat mixture; cover and steam 10 minutes or until eggplant is tender.
Remove cover and place cheese on top of eggplant slices.
Place lid back on skillet and turn off heat. When cheese is melted, serve on rice.

title: italian chicken
directions: Place chicken in a bowl with wine, oil, oregano and garlic powder.
Place skin side down in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Put in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes. Turn over.
Sprinkle with more bread crumbs.
Cook until crispy.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, making sure there is plenty of juice. Put in baking dish. Top with bacon strips. Bake at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until onion is cooked.

title: sausage lentil soup
directions: Combine ingredients in a 6-quart kettle.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour, then uncovered for 30 minutes to thicken.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a medium bowl.
Beat for 10 minutes.
Put vanilla wafer in paper baking cup flat side down one to a cup and fill 3/4
with cheese mixture.
Bake for 17 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely.
Top with filling of your choice.

title: linda's apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Combine sugar, juice, flour and egg in saucepan.
Blend well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash and quarter apples.
Use only about 1/2 of apple juice or apple cider.
Cook over low heat until they are soft.
Use food mill to separate the pulp from the peeling and seeds.
Mix and cook over very low heat until all juice is cooked out.
It will probably take several hours.
Put in jars and seal.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine salad oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Gradually add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add grated carrots.
Mix well.
Turn into three 8-inch layer cake pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 60 minutes. Remove from pans and cool on racks.
When completely cool, fill and frost with Nut Icing.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. (Lower heat as needed.) Mix 1 can mashed up tomatoes in ground beef. Add onion, crumble biscuits in and mix well. Add eggs, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Mix and add 1/2 bottle ketchup. Form into a loaf. Add remaining ketchup on top of the loaf. Bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, cream of tartar and sugar.
Cut in shortening until like coarse crumbs.
Make a well; add 2/3 cup milk all at once.
Stir quickly with fork just until dough follows fork around bowl.
Turn onto lightly floured surface. Knead gently 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll or pat dough 1/2-inch thick. Dip 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter in flour.
Cut dough straight down. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pecan chicken
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 sheets of waxed paper and flatten with a rolling pin.
Combine honey and mustard and spread on both sides of chicken.
Dredge in chopped pecans. Arrange in lightly greased shallow dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes until done.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in covered bowl.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: greek shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large skillet, heat olive oil; saute onions and garlic until onion is soft.
Add parsley, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and saute for 2 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Stir in red pepper.
Place mixture in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or just until cheese melts and is bubbly.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: how to preserve children
directions: Mix the children and dogs well together; put them on the field, stirring constantly.
Pour the brook over the pebbles. Sprinkle the field with flowers.
Spread over all a deep blue sky and bake in the sun.
When brown, set away to cool in the bath tub.
And don't be afraid to make them mind you.
They will not break or go mad.

title: flounder casserole
directions: Combine soup, Miracle Whip, milk and cheese; blend well.
Stir in flounder, peas, noodles and onion.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: everlast yeast
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in warm area to rise until ready to use to bake with.
Keep 1/2 of the amount for a "start" next time.
Feed with the same ingredients for the next baking.
Each time remember to keep half and use half. Refrigerate.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Blend in shortening with a fork.
Combine egg, pineapple and sugar and add to the mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix together 1 cup buttermilk and vanilla pudding.
Add 1 can crushed pineapple (16 ounces), drained, 1 can mandarin oranges, drained and 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Just before serving add 14 Keebler fudge stripe cookies broken in pieces.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: *Or use, 1 1/2 cups whole wheat flour and 1 1/2 cups white flour.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add flavorings; beat well. Cook in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: golf balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and make into 1-inch balls.
Melt wax and chocolate together.
Dip balls into chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: cracker jack cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and brown sugar in bowl.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in oats, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Beat eggs, water and Jell-O for 1 minute.
Add cake mix and beat 3 more minutes.
Add oil and beat 1 minute.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until top springs back when pressed lightly.
Remove from oven and slightly pierce cake all over with fork holes.
Mix together the powdered sugar and lemon juice; pour over the top of the cake.
Makes one 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: bob's coconut cake
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut and store overnight. The next day, bake cake according to package directions.
Cool. Split each layer in half to make total of 4 layers.
Frost with sour cream mixture and store in refrigerator for at least 4 days before serving.
Tastes just like Grandma's homemade coconut cake.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Blend soup and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in chicken, celery, onion and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Fill 9-inch pie plate 2/3 full of sliced apples.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Mix remaining ingredients together and put mixture on top of apples by spoonful. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: summer squash delight
directions: Cut squash lengthwise and boil for 5 minutes.
Scoop out seeds.
Bring 2 cups of spinach to a boil, drain when completed. Combine together spinach, chopped onion and sour cream. Place spinach inside each piece of squash.
Sprinkle on bread crumbs, lightly.
