Finally top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Thoroughly cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flour.
Mix well.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Pour into pie shell and sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Pie is done when knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: peanut butter breakfast bar
directions: Preheat oven to 325° .
Combine eggs, honey and chunky peanut butter.
Add dry milk and mix until well blended.
Add cereal mix and stir until coated evenly.
Spread in a lightly greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into 6 even bars. Wrap individually and store in refrigerator.

title: cheddar cheese chips
directions: Process cheese and butter. Add flour and pepper.
Cut into 3 sausage type rolls.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Cut into 1/8-inch chips.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix in order given and bake for 20 minutes in a greased pan. Set oven at 375°.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, sour cream, milk and 2 cups Cool Whip.
Beat with wire whisk until blended.
Spoon half of the filling into crust.
Put berries on top.
Cover with remaining filling.
Freeze for 1 hour or chill in fridge for 3 hours.
Put Cool Whip on top and garnish with strawberries.

title: hamburgers to grill
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make 6 patties and wrap in bacon.
Secure with toothpicks.
Put on hot grill 15 minutes or more.
Make patties 1/2-inch to 3/4-inch thick (can precook bacon a little).

title: standard muffin
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bubba's "hot" jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, pepper and garlic in butter for about 5 minutes. Add chili powder and cumin; stir well.
Add all the other ingredients and cook for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli and sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: open-faced sandwiches
directions: Mix well and spread thin layer on halves of buttered hamburger buns.
Broil open-faced until done.
You may want to put on lower rack for 5 minutes or so to be sure underside of meat mixture is cooked.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Cook and drain hamburger meat.
In a crock-pot, mix beans, tomatoes, Ro-Tel, milk, cheese and hamburger meat. Cook on low heat for 1 to 2 hours, stirring often. Serve over chips.
Great for parties!

title: chicken picante
directions: In a small bowl, combine salsa, mustard and lime juice.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine butter, water and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and beat in flour, sugar, salt, eggs, sour cream, soda and vanilla. Pour into large cookie sheet with sides. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cynthia's squash dressing
directions: Cook 35 to 45 minutes in 2-quart casserole at 350° to 375°.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix together the hamburger, bacon and onion.
Mix together the remaining ingredients; add to meat.
Stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cover and bake 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, egg, onion, broccoli and cheese. Put in a casserole dish.
Mix margarine well with stuffing; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sierra chili
directions: Brown beef in Crisco and seasoned salt. Add beef broth, tomato sauce and water to cover plus 1-inch (add more water as needed). Cook on low 1/2 hour. Add next 8 ingredients. Slow bubble about 1 hour or until meat is tender. Add remaining 6 ingredients. Slow cook for 45 minutes. Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: cheezy macaroni
directions: Add oil to 5-quarts boiling water.
Stir in macaroni.
Melt 1 stick of butter or margarine in double boiler.
Add Cheddar cheese soup, 8 to 10 slices of American cheese and 1/2 block Cheddar cheese (stir into a fondue).
Rinse cooked macaroni in cold water. Pour into well oiled aluminum wrapped pan.
Stir in beaten eggs, milk and fondue mix.
Fold in Ricotta, shred rest of American cheese and remaining Cracker Barrel sharp cheese into top of macaroni.
Garnish with paprika.
Bake until bubbles, 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix together.
Make two layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and split layers with a thread.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onions and seasonings (mixture will be thick).
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place biscuits in a greased muffin pan.
Press to sides and bottom.
Spoon mixture into cups. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until brown.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Makes 1 pie; double to make 2 pies.
Mix Dream Whip up according to directions in a deep bowl.
In separate bowl, mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Next, mix the Dream Whip with the cream cheese sugar mixture.
In a pie pan, place on all sides and bottom, the vanilla wafers to be the crust.
Fill with the cream cheese/Dream Whip mixture. On top, spoon blueberry topping and chill.

title: shrimp substantial salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and let stand until partially set.

title: lox quiche
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add lox.
Mix half and half, eggs, sugar, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
(Mix well with electric mixer.)

title: mona's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Rub margarine on the inside of a large casserole dish.

title: low-fat banana split cake
directions: Spread crushed graham crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with mixed pudding; chill.
Layer bananas over chilled pudding.
Layer strawberries, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Contains 4 grams fat per serving.

title: spicy tortilla chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Brush each tortilla with 1/4 teaspoon oil. Cut each tortilla into 8 triangles. Place triangles on a large nonstick baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Combine salt and cumin; sprinkle over triangles. Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes or until triangles begin to lightly brown at edges. Remove from oven; cool. Yields 4 servings (serving size 8 chips).

title: tangy pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake 1 tablespoon flour in browning bag; trim fat from meat; season with salt.
Place in bag and put in pan.
Place a slice of onion and a slice of pepper on each chop.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour in bag.
Follow browning bag instructions; cook 1 hour or until tested tender.

title: peanut butter granola
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins; let stand 10 minutes, drain. In saucepan, combine peanut butter, honey and cinnamon.
Heat through.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Place oats in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Pour warm mixture over oats and stir gently until mixture is coated.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 35 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Stir in dates, raisins and nuts.
Let dry in oven 1 1/2 hours.
Store in airtight container.

title: molasses gingersnaps
directions: Cream together oil,
eggs
and	sugar.	Sift flour with soda, cinnamon and ginger.
Mix
well;
form
dough into small balls. Roll into sugar.
Place
on
cookie sheet. Bake in 325° oven for 12 to 14 minutes or until top cracks.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: Sift together the flours, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in margarine.
Mix yeast with warm water.
Add yeast mixture, honey and buttermilk to dry ingredients.
Knead 5 to 10 times on a floured surface.
Roll and cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake on a greased baking sheet for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: diet oatmeal applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put mixture in a Bundt pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions and let it cool. Spread drained pineapple over cake.
Whip pudding with 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Mix well.
Spread this over pineapple.
Top with a layer of whipped topping.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over all, if desired.

title: chicken dumpling
directions: Cook chicken until tender; remove chicken.
Add chicken broth, butter and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil, then cut biscuits into strips and put into broth.
Cook until halfway through and add chicken.
Cook for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: party punch
directions: Add cold water to hot Jell-O before adding juices.
Just before serving, add 2 large bottles of ginger ale.
Makes 2 gallons and 1 quart.
Add sherbet if you want to.

title: ham and cheese spread
directions: Combine cream cheese with sour cream, Ranch dressing mix and honey.
Fold in ham and cheese.
Serve with chips or snack crackers.

title: stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf and gravy
directions: Mix beef, crackers, eggs, tenderizer, garlic powder, catsup, mushrooms, onion and salt and pepper. Form a loaf and fit into a greased 9 x 13 pan.

title: homemade cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Next, add sour cream and vanilla.
Add Cool Whip and blend well.
Pour into the pie crust.
Chill for 5 hours.
Garnish with fresh fruit as desired.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients except Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 1/2 of the mixture until set.
Spread Cool Whip on top of the set Jell-O.
Then pour the rest of Jell-O mixture over the Cool Whip.
Chill until set.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box.
Pour in sheet pan and cook. Let stand 5 minutes.
Punch holes in top with toothpick.
Pour milk and coconut mixture on top.
Put Cool Whip on top of that; finish with coconut.

title: aunt edna's punch
directions: Mix
Jell-O
and
sugar
with
a
little water; stir to dissolve, then add other ingredients and add up to 1 gallon of water.

title: japanese mandarin orange refrigerator cake
directions: Drain juice from oranges.
Add enough water to make 2 cups and bring to a boil.
Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid.
Add cold water and cool until mixture is syrupy.
Line bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Fold syrupy mixture into whipped cream with oranges, reserving a sufficient quantity of the segments for garnishing.
Pour into lined cake pan and chill for several hours or overnight.
Makes 10 servings.

title: lenten chocolate cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, water, vinegar and vanilla and mix well. Sift together flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add dry ingredients to liquid mixture and mix well.
Do not use electric mixer; just hand mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
When cool, cover with powdered sugar.

title: layered fruit dessert
directions: Arrange crackers in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
Evenly layer banana and strawberries over crackers.
In large bowl, combine dry pudding mix, dry milk, undrained pineapple and water. Mix well using wire whisk.
Evenly spoon pudding mixture over fruit.
Refrigerate for at least 20 minutes.
Cut into 6 servings.

title: tasty banana bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease 9 x 13 inch pan.
In a large bowl, blend first 5 ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes on high. Pour into pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan as directed on box.
Spread pineapple (including juice) on warm cake.
Mix instant pudding mix, milk and softened cream cheese.
Spread over pineapple, then spread Cool Whip on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in shortening; drain fat.
Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Over low heat, combine pineapple with juice and Heinz 57 sauce.
Pour over pork chops.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes over low heat or until chops are tender.
Add green pepper strips and cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes more.
Thicken sauce, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain. Add first 6 ingredients. Cook manicotti according to package. Fill each manicotti with meat mixture. Place manicotti in greased baking dish. Top with spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove foil and bake 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In large skillet, put chicken, water, bouillon, wine and mustard.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Mix flour with milk or yogurt.
Stir into sauce.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Garnish with parsley (optional).
Serve over pasta or noodles.

title: yummy ambrosia
directions: Peel and cut up
oranges
in chunks; add pineapple with juice, coconut and marshmallows.
Mix in sour cream and sugar. Refrigerate.

title: onion beef stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef with salt, pepper, allspice and nutmeg.
Set aside in large bowl.
Melt 1/2 of the butter in pan drippings.
Stir in onion and celery; cook until tender.
Stir in remaining butter and water and bring to a boil. Pour on meat mixture and mix in celery leaves and bread cubes. Chill, then stuff turkey when ready to cook.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put soup with milk in large bowl.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in buttered casserole. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oyster cracker nibbles
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together well.
Pour over the oyster crackers.
Stir off and on for several hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar (dressing).
Add to salad ingredients and chill.

title: easy and pretty vegetable dish
directions: Follow cooking directions on package and drain.
Place vegetables in a glass dish.
Brown seasoned bread crumbs on top of stove in skillet.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle enough bread crumbs to cover vegetable dish.
Place in oven until hot.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Be careful.
Do not allow to burn.

title: strawberry margarita
directions: Place the limeade, beer, tequila, ice cubes and sliced strawberries in a blender.
Whirl until the ice is crushed.
Pour into 4 large wine glasses; garnish with lime slices and whole strawberries.
Serves 4.

title: monterey chicken
directions: Slice peppers in 1/2-inch strips; slice mushrooms and set aside.
Dip thinly sliced chicken in milk.
Shake off excess milk and pat on bread crumbs.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in frypan on medium heat.
Saute chicken breasts until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Wipe pan out with paper towel and heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add green peppers and mushrooms.
Saute about 10 minutes. Add white wine and cook another 10 minutes until wine is reduced, but pepper is still crunchy.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Cover with sauteed vegetables and juices and spread shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Add soup and sauce.
Simmer. Mix noodles with meat.
Put in casserole dish.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake in 375° oven until cheese melts.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and potatoes.
Then add eggs, milk, chocolate and flour mixed with spices and baking powder.
Last, add cherries and nuts.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: golden pound cake for two
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add extracts and juice.
Mix, then add milk combining thoroughly. Mix in dry ingredients.
Add eggs and beat well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 1/2 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean. Cool.

title: simple chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding enough mayonnaise to make the right consistency for salad.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Spread mixture on both sides of buns.
Place ham and cheese on buns.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Can be frozen.
May make ahead and refrigerate, if so, heat 5 minutes.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in large bowl.
Dissolve 2 packages yeast in 3 cups warm water.
Add to mixture.
Mix well by hand.
Stir in 8 to 10 cups self-rising flour (2 cups at a time), adding just enough for easy handling.
Cover; let rise in bowl until double.
Punch down.
Roll and cut as for biscuits.
Place in greased pans.
Cover.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Also can be made into cinnamon rolls or loaves of bread.

title: darlene's sweet dough dinner rolls
directions: In one bowl, combine margarine and boiling water.
In another bowl, beat eggs with sugar, salt and cold water.
Combine the two mixtures.

title: beet pickles
directions: Heat and pour over beets and let set at least 48 hours.

title: antipasto napoli
directions: Combine tomatoes, mushrooms, sausage, zucchini and artichokes.
Add dressing; cover and marinate in refrigerator 2 hours or more.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Toss vegetables with greens.
Serve with remaining marinade.
Sprinkle with grated Romano.

title: good morning coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, granulated sugar and salt; cut in margarine until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture to remaining crumb mixture.
Add baking powder.
Stir, then milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 25 minutes.

title: berry sauce for chicken
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except berries, for 3 minutes in small pan.
Add berries.
Serve over chicken.
(Boneless is best.)

title: italian meat sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot; stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: 4 steps to heaven
directions: In an oblong baking dish, put ingredients.

title: chocolate sherbet(low-cal)
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, gelatin and salt in saucepan.
With wire whisk beat in milk.
Stir over low heat until gelatin and sugar are dissolved.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Freeze 4 hours or until firm but not hard.
Turn into bowl and beat with mixer until smooth.
Pour in freezer container, cover and freeze until hard.
Serves 8.

title: chewy peanut butter caramel balls
directions: Melt caramels and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Add melted peanut butter.
Mix in crushed cereal.
Roll into small balls and then into powdered sugar.
Store in cool, dry place.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry and flute edges.
Mix together sugar, butter, flour, salt, lemon peel and juice.
Beat egg yolks.
Combine with milk.
Stir in lemon mix.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into lemon mixture.
Place in crust. Bake on lowest shelf at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes, until top is richly brown and set when lightly touched.
Serve at room temperature or chill as long as 6 hours.
Serves 6.

title: beef casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper, beef and mushrooms.
Add gravy and pour over the cooked noodles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake in moderate oven 30-45 minutes.

title: cornbread for two
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients in a small bowl; add egg, milk and 1 tablespoon melted shortening.
Mix together until smooth.
Pour into hot iron skillet containing the other 1 tablespoon shortening.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: lime float
directions: Put 2 big scoops of lime sherbet into a big glass, then pour ginger ale over lime sherbet slowly.
If not, it will bubble over. Please enjoy.
Good nighttime snack.

title: "caviar pie" appetizer
directions: Divide the cream cheese in four equal parts.
Mix together parsley or dill, onions and cornichons or capers.
Line a 6-inch round or small fish mold with clear plastic wrap.
Put 1/4 cheese in bottom of the bowl.
Top with 1/3 of the salmon, then sprinkle with 1/3 of the onion mixture.
Repeat twice more.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and press down on mold to even out the mixture.
Chill.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil. Add sugar; stir until dissolves. Pour into cartons and freeze. When ready to use, pour ginger ale or Mountain Dew over frozen punch to taste.

title: mocha oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, other ingredients and oats last. Work together well.
Chill overnight.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in chopped walnuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush
Oreo
cookies
in blender until fine.
Pour some into bottom
of	flowerpot;
cream
together cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth (set aside).
Mix together pudding as instructed on package until thickened.
Add cream cheese to pudding.
Blend together until well blended.
Add Cool Whip to pudding
mixture and blend together.
Put pudding mixture in a flowerpot;	layer
cookies	and pudding, saving enough crushed Oreos
to
completely
cover top of flowerpot.
Add artificial flower and gummy worms as desired.	Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: basic cream puffs
directions: Combine water and butter.
Bring to a boil over medium heat in a saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring vigorously, until dough forms a smooth ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat vigorously until mixture is
smooth and glossy.
Spoon 6 mounds of dough 3 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425 degrees.
Prick puffs with sharp knife and cool for 1 hour.
Split each puff and fill with ice cream, pudding, or whipped cream.
Top with chocolate syrup and/or peanuts.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until almost tender.
Mix as in order given. Bake 45 minutes.
Put cornflakes and melted butter on top when almost done baking.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix onions and cheese.
Cut up boiled chicken.
Dip tortillas into enchilada sauce (prepared according to package directions). Fill with chicken, cheese, onions, tomatoes and olives.
Roll up and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the remaining sauce over top and sprinkle with grated Jack cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli as package directs, only until thawed.
Put in blender until finely chopped.
Saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk in gradual amounts, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Add seasonings and bouillon.
Add broccoli; simmer.
Makes 8 cups.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese; bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: tartare sauce
directions: Mix all together.
If too thick, use milk to thin.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, onion and bell pepper.
Add eggs and bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place bacon strips on bottom of pan.
Mold meat loaf to fit over bacon.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
When meat loaf is halfway done, top with ketchup and finish cooking.
Let meat loaf set 10 minutes before slicing.

title: meat filled mushroom caps
directions: Marinate mushrooms
in	soy
sauce
for
hour.
Chop stems. Mix ground beef, green pepper, bread crumbs, egg yolk, onion, garlic
salt
and
pepper.	Drain caps, stuff and mound high. Brush tops with soy sauce and broil 8 to 10 minutes and freeze. Bring to room temperature and bake at 350° (preheated oven) for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add green pepper and onion; cook until tender.
Add spices, potatoes, tomatoes and tomato sauce; cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Add drained corn and kidney beans; simmer 15 minutes more.

title: italian herb potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Place in microwave dish. Drizzle with olive oil.
Sprinkle with seasonings through pepper. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes or until tender, stirring once.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Microwave 1 minute longer.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Simmer tomato juice with seasonings, sugar, onion on low heat 15 minutes.
Strain juice, add softened gelatin and lemon juice, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Cool, then pour into individual oiled molds.
Chill until firm (about 2 hours).
Double amount of this recipe to fill a 9-inch mold.

title: strawberry pretzel salad(student favorite)
directions: Mix pretzels and sugar.
Press in oblong pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
(Watch carefully.)
Cool.
Cream the softened cream cheese and mix with sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour over cooled pretzel crust, making sure the mixture goes to the edges.
Cool. Dissolve jello in boiling water; add fruit.
Chill until thick. Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Cut ends off of wings.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over wings.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle over top of cake dry chocolate pudding mix.
Pour over all 1 c. boiling water.
Bake cake as directed on cake box.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, make a white sauce with the first 5 ingredients.
In a greased 2-quart casserole, place half of the sliced potatoes, half of the onion and half of the white sauce. Repeat the layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer with American cheese, if desired. Serves 4 to 6.

title: potatoes and carrots au gratin
directions: In a greased 2-quart casserole, place potatoes, carrots, green pepper and onion.
Combine half the cheese and remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and gently toss.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until tender.
Top with remaining cheese and bake, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes more. Serves 6.

title: oatmeal apple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add oatmeal and fruits; add sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven.

title: apricot bran muffins
directions: Oil muffin pans.
Fork stir all dry ingredients together. Drain apricots and blend on low speed.
Add oil and egg; blend well.
Stir blender mixture into dry ingredients mixing to moisten. Stir in chopped apricots.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins and they freeze well.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine, sugars, eggs, vanilla and pudding until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour and baking soda. Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: homestyle banana bread
directions: Beat together mashed banana, oil, eggs and water until creamy. Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices.
Beat well. Stir in chopped walnuts.
Spoon batter into an oiled and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool completely before slicing.
Serves 6.
Approximately 1 bread and 1 fruit exchanges.

title: best split pea soup
directions: Cook peas, water, bay leaf and salt for 3 to 4 hours. Saute in olive oil, onions, garlic, celery, potato and carrots and add to mix. Fifteen minutes before serving, add wine, mustard, thyme and sesame oil. Just before serving, add parsley and vinegar.

title: chocolate peanut butter cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine
graham cracker crumbs, cocoa, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter (or margarine), mixing well. Spread evenly over bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan (or two 9-inch pie pans).
Bake crust for 10 minutes.
Let cool. Reduce oven temperature to 300°.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar and water in a heavy 12-inch skillet. Place over medium heat and bring mixture to a boil.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture has caramelized and nuts are coated (skillet should appear dry when stirring through mixture), about 12 to 15 minutes.
Immediately spread coated nuts on a large buttered baking sheet.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Store cooled peanuts in an airtight container.

title: swiss ham ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine parsley, onion, mustard, margarine and lemon juice.
Add cheese, ham and broccoli; set aside.
Separate crescent rolls.
On greased cookie sheet, arrange with points out in a circle with bases overlapping.
Spoon mixture onto bases.
Fold points over and tuck under bases.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can be made ahead, covered and refrigerated up to 3 hours.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the butter over low heat.
Add the flour and mix well.
Then add the liquids.
Increase the heat to medium and allow to cook for a few minutes, stirring often to prevent sticking until it begins to thicken.
Add the broccoli, onion and garlic powder.
Allow to cook for an additional 15 minutes.
Add the cheese and cook for another 5 minutes.
You can garnish with additional grated cheese or croutons if you desire.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and beat eggs, milk, oil and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients, beating for 2 minutes.
Then add water. Batter will be thin.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) pans or in 30 cupcakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (less for cupcakes).
Cool and frost.

title: chocolate dessert waffles
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in waffle iron.
Serve with ice cream and hot fudge or caramel.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: In bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Shape into ball and roll in nuts.
Wrap and refrigerate until chilled (overnight).

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin, salt, cinnamon and clove in boiling water. Add cranberry sauce.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in oranges, apples and walnuts.
Pour into a 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm (about 4 hours).

title: cucumber relish
directions: Put cucumbers and onions in colander; drain 1 hour.
Bring sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed to boiling point and add drained cucumbers and onions; simmer about 20 minutes.
Fill sterilized pint jars; seal.
Yields about 6 pints.

title: gingerbread houses
directions: Cover a cardboard tray with aluminum foil.
Put frosting in bowl with confectioners sugar and mix thoroughly.
Frost the outside of a milk carton.
Cover with graham cracker "bricks."
Use frosting to attach candies and cereals for decorating.
Use cake decorator to pipe on icicles and designs.
Attach to board with frosting.
Continue decorating until you have your own gingerbread town.
Experiment with different shaped boxes and cans to build condos, castles and churches.
(Ice cream cones make great trees when covered with green frosting.)
Use your imagination and create a great, edible holiday centerpiece!

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, put in pie shell.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours, then serve.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix in order all ingredients and roll out.
Cut with doughnut cutter. Drop into hot grease.
(Original recipe was used in black frying pan; can also use Fry Daddy.)

title: low calorie cocoa drink
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large cup.
Add boiling water and stir well.
Serve.
Makes 1 serving.
One serving equals 20 calories or 1/2 fat exchange.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Stir
together over low heat the oleo, cheese and half and half until just combined.
Pour over frozen hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: summery tomato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium size serving bowl.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Makes 4 servings.
Can be made 3 days ahead.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 c. Cool Whip until smooth.
Spread over crust.
Mix chocolate pudding with 1 1/2 c. cold milk until thick.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Prepare the vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 c. milk.
Spread over chocolate pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: corn flake goodies
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, stirring, until melted.
Add corn flakes and stir until coated.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: chocolate sheet cake #3
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Bring to boil in saucepan the margarine, water and cocoa.
Remove boiling water from heat and pour into flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 12 x 17 x 1 1/2-inch jelly roll pan (batter will be thin) and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: nun's cake(prize winning recipe)
directions: Cream butter or butter substitute.
Add sugar and yolks of eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir in unbeaten whites of eggs and beat mixture.
Sift flour, measure, and sift with baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Sprinkle on caraway seed, beat well, and add flavorings.
Pour into well-oiled loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 1 hour.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Crack the egg into a bowl; beat well.
Add 1/4 cup of tomato soup and stir well.
Measure the uncooked rice, parsley flakes, dried onion, salt and pepper.
Add to egg-soup mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Add ground beef.
Mix well.
Shape meat mixture into 1-inch meatballs.
Put into a skillet and brown.
Put water into a small mixing bowl and add the rest of the soup.
Measure Worcestershire sauce; add to the mixing bowl.
Stir well.
Pour soup mixture over the meatballs.
When mixture starts to boil, turn burner to low heat.
Cover skillet with a lid.
Cook for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine in blender.
Refrigerate several hours.
Use as dip with bite-sized pieces of fresh fruit.

title: rutabaga casserole
directions: Cook the peeled, cubed rutabaga until soft in slightly salted water.
Put through blender or processor.
Let breadcrumbs swell in cream; add to rutabaga.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add syrup and nutmeg.
Add a bit of cooking broth, if too thick.

title: glazed peach pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and nutmeg. Stir in water, lemon juice and pureed peaches.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly about 5 minutes or until mixture is thickened.
Pour all but 1/2 cup of glaze into the pie shell.
Top with sliced peaches and brush with reserved glaze.
Chill for at least 3 hours.
